    {
      "id": "73f113a4-a7e1-4ea4-980e-f20da7a9e7b2",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "The heavy velvet drapes brush your shoulder as you move into the pool of amber light cast by the wall sconces. The smell of burnt sage hangs thick in the air here, masking the salt tang from the balcony. Valerius flinches at the sound of your voice, his hand jerking spasmodically to cover the lead box, though his palm is too small to hide it entirely. He wipes a bead of sweat from his upper lip with the back of a knuckle, his eyes darting from the box to you and then quickly away, fixing on a point somewhere near your left ear.\n\n\"Not at all,\" Valerius says, his voice pitching higher than before, thin and brittle. \"Just... reviewing some old debts. Isn't that right, Hestus?\" The Elaphine turns his head slowly, his neck muscles rolling beneath the fur. He doesn't look at Valerius. His dark, liquid eyes lock onto yours, unblinking and calculating. He dips his muzzle in a gesture that is half-bow, half-challenge, the tip of his tongue briefly tasting the air as if he can scent the intrigue clinging to your silk sleeves.\n\n\"Old debts are the hardest to collect,\" Hestus rumbles, his voice a deep, chest-vibrating thrum that seems to rattle the wine glass on the table. He shifts his weight, the iron-shod hoof of his left leg clicking sharply against the floorboards. Valerius clears his throat, a wet, hacking sound, and straightens his doublet, trying to compose the mask of a bored councilor, but his fingers remain white-knuckled around the edge of the table. The lead box sits between you like a bomb with a lit fuse.",
