    {
      "id": "ee8fe1a0-0404-4c7d-9e1b-675538ec6428",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Valerius lets out a sharp, barking laugh that dies in his throat, his eyes widening as he realizes how loud it sounds in the quiet room. He snatches his wine glass and takes a long, deep draught, the dark liquid staining his lips, before wiping his mouth with a trembling hand. \"Negotiation? There is no negotiation here. Just... just a private accounting. A tedious matter of ledgers and tariffs that hardly concerns a guest of your standing.\"\n\nHe moves to block your path to the table, his body language shifting from nervous to defensive, but he is too slow. Hestus ignores him entirely, stepping around the councilor with a heavy, deliberate gait. The Elaphine’s shadow falls over you, carrying the scent of damp wool and pine needles. He doesn't offer the box; he merely rests a heavy, three-fingered hand atop it, his claws tapping a slow, rhythmic beat against the lead.\n\n\"Tariffs do not scream, little human,\" Hestus says softly, his dark eyes boring into yours with an intensity that disregards Valerius entirely. \"And old debts do not bear the mark of the Broken Sun. Valerius buys silence. I am looking for a buyer who understands the cargo.\" From the harbor below, the deep, resonant bell of the Arsenal begins to toll the hour, the vibrations humming through the floorboards and rattling the wine in Valerius's glass.",
