    {
      "id": "893c3535-a4a1-432f-b8cc-ba20dfc2f999",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The Aegis**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**The Aegis**\n\nThe Aegis are an artificial race of sentient machines. Their form is made of a type of light that can have physical impact on their world, their 'core' being a highly complex chip varying in power depending on the Aegis' rank and Type. They were created by the United Empire and designed in humanity's image — which has consequences the Empire never anticipated.\n\nThe Aegis are capable of using magic, though their SOULs are not natural, instead being artificially created. This makes their capacity for magic much lower than that of natural beings, though they are capable of using technology to augment their magic capacity, having much more advanced technology than Terrans.\n\nHowever, the Aegis are bound by failsafes built into them by the United Empire — they cannot harm humans. This constraint extends to any action taken with intent to harm, preventing workarounds such as arming beastfolk against humanity. This is the true reason the Aegis remain on the moon rather than conquering Terra.\n\nFurthermore, Aegis technology operates on principles incompatible with Terra's magic-saturated environment. Their devices malfunction, their weapons misfire, and their light-bodies may destabilize in high-magic areas. To bridge this gap, they would need to study a natural human SOUL — but capturing a human for study constitutes harm, creating a perfect catch-22 that has trapped PRIMA for a millennium.",
