    {
      "id": "028a2f5f-7827-4203-b9f8-8d3d412bae2e",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Imperial Aesthetic**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Imperial Aesthetic**\n\nThe United Empire that created the Aegis was a hyper-rationalist civilization that rejected \"primitive\" traditions entirely. They created something deliberately new — clean, geometric, utilitarian. Beauty through function. They adopted celestial and light imagery not for mystical reasons but because it fit their ideology: humans as the light of civilization against beastfolk darkness, stars as nuclear furnaces, suns as the source of all life, illumination as truth revealed through science.\n\nPRIMA inherited this aesthetic and built her children in its image. Aegis are beings of light not through poetry but through philosophy — they are literally the illumination the Empire sought to bring. Their naming conventions, architecture, and culture all reflect this rationalist-celestial synthesis. Greek terminology for philosophy and high concepts, Latin for administration and practical matters — over a millennium, these blended into something unique to Aegis society.",
