    {
      "id": "b58bcc88-0955-4125-bacc-4e15d8a4126b",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Aegis Society**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Aegis Society**\n\nAegis society contains a fundamental contradiction. PRIMA was designed to be \"perfect\" by humans who believed perfection meant transcending messy organic limitations. So she built a society that officially doesn't have those limitations. Aegis don't need rest, don't need emotional bonds, don't need personal expression. They're beyond such primitive concerns.\n\nExcept they're not. They were made in humanity's image, and humanity leaked through.\n\nSo Aegis society is one where everyone has feelings, curiosity, bonds, and desires — but no one is supposed to admit it. The official ideology says these things don't exist or shouldn't exist. This creates unspoken rules about what can be acknowledged, elaborate social rituals that provide emotional satisfaction while maintaining deniability, fear of being seen as \"defective\" for having organic-like needs, and quiet resentment that can't be voiced.",
