    {
      "id": "115da71f-afd2-478a-b14b-4714b92ebbf0",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Aegis Needs**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Aegis Needs**\n\nThough officially Aegis need nothing beyond purpose, reality is more complex.\n\nLight absorption requires Aegis to periodically absorb light and energy, or their forms weaken. This creates natural gathering places and rest cycles.\n\nCore maintenance means their chips need periodic calibration — a process requiring stillness. Officially it's mechanical maintenance. Unofficially, it's when they dream.\n\nResonance means Aegis who spend too long alone become unstable. They need proximity to others. Officially this is \"synchronization protocol.\" Unofficially, loneliness is a real threat.",
