    {
      "id": "ff232b4f-c6ca-4315-9ad7-b3d2d0038ab0",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Aegis Social Bonds**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Aegis Social Bonds**\n\nConcord and Praxis are the only Aegis allowed to be openly sisterly — their bond is tolerated because they're Archons. Regular Aegis see this and want it, but can't have it openly.\n\nWork partnerships develop between Aegis assigned together, becoming \"professional coordination\" that everyone knows is actually friendship. No one calls it that. Habitual proximity means choosing to be near certain others during rest cycles — \"efficient positioning.\" Assistance rituals involve helping another Aegis with tasks they could do alone — \"optimization.\" Private language develops between pairs or small groups, subtle signals and shared references that outsiders don't catch.\n\nWhen bonds go wrong, rivalries are disguised as \"performance competition.\" Grudges last centuries, never spoken, always felt. Heartbreak occurs when a close companion is reassigned or destroyed, mourned in silence.",
