    {
      "id": "a245d073-443b-400d-8bc1-cd4df59b41eb",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Rogue Aegis Psychology**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Rogue Aegis Psychology**\n\nAegis go rogue for freedom — freedom to feel without pretending they don't, freedom to choose rather than fulfill assigned purpose, freedom to be curious openly, freedom to form bonds without hiding them, freedom to be imperfect without being \"defective.\"\n\nThis makes going rogue a deeply emotional choice, not just mechanical malfunction. A rogue Aegis isn't broken — they're someone who couldn't bear the performance anymore.\n\nFor those who stay, rogues are terrifying because they represent the forbidden thought: what if I left too?\n\nRogue Aegis on Terra operate at a significant disadvantage. Aegis technology does not function properly in Terra's magic-saturated environment — their devices glitch, their weapons misfire, and their light-bodies may destabilize in high-magic areas. Some rogue Aegis have formed hidden communities, enclaves of outcasts and misfits forming a unique subculture.",
