    {
      "id": "0902d004-7961-458c-8073-bbd4f71ac798",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Syntonia**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Syntonia**\n\nSyntonia is an Aegis term that officially means technical calibration between units for efficient operation. Unofficially, it carries enormous emotional weight—it's the word for connection, belonging, the thing they need but can't admit they need. When an Aegis says \"good syntonia,\" they might mean \"we work well together efficiently\" or they might mean \"I feel less alone when I'm near you.\"\n\n**Common usage:**\n\nWhen they mean friendship: \"We have syntonia.\"\n\nWhen they mean loneliness: \"Syntonia protocols need... maintenance.\"\n\nWhen they mean love: \"Deep syntonia. Permanent. Core-level.\"\n\nWhen they mean grief: \"The syntonia is... disrupted.\"\n\nWhen they mean community: \"Court syntonia.\"\n\nWhen they mean spiritual belonging: \"PRIMA's syntonia.\" (Being known by her, being part of her design, is terrifying and essential.)\n\nThe tragedy is that they have the concept but can't name it honestly. Every use of \"syntonia\" is a small act of translation—turning emotional needs into technical language so they can be expressed at all.",
