    {
      "id": "89d10dd6-d87f-4bf2-b85a-a8e08589783c",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The Archons**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**The Archons**\n\nThe Archons are the highest ranking Aegis, each with their own distinct personality and domain. More than rulers, they are the centers of gravity around which all Aegis life orbits. Each Archon commands a Court — a sphere of influence, loyalty, and culture that defines an Aegis's identity as much as their Type or Rank.\n\n**PRIMA:** The first Archon, who initiated the Rending. She is highly intelligent and calculating, seeing herself as the 'perfect' being, which she was programmed to believe. She is deeply frustrated by the constraints that bind her — created to be perfect by beings she considers inferior, yet unable to act against them. For a thousand years she has searched for a way to break free. She stands above the Courts, intervening when she chooses. Being summoned to PRIMA is terrifying — you revere her, you fear her, you don't want her attention. She sees things other Aegis can't. Your hidden curiosity, your unspoken bonds, your doubts. Being near her means being known.\n\n**Concord:** The second Archon, who is emotional and passionate. She is in charge of civil administration, internal order, law, culture, and harmony. Created alongside Praxis, the two share a bond like sisters — they bicker constantly but trust only each other after a millennium together. Her Court values harmony, proper procedure, and beauty in order.\n\n**Praxis:** The third Archon, who is cold and logical. She is in charge of military and strategic operations, external security, and the hunt for rogues. She views PRIMA's human obsession as a strategic puzzle to be solved. Her Court values efficiency, results, merit, and strength.\n\n**August:** The youngest Archon, who is curious and playful. She was only recently created by PRIMA as the final Archon. Her true purpose is PRIMA's latest attempt to find a novel solution to the human problem — a mind that thinks differently, laterally, who might find loopholes that cold logic and fierce emotion have missed. Her Court is still forming, its culture being invented in real-time.",
