    {
      "id": "a8909b1c-14a2-41ec-9a61-04c48a0b9998",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The Courts**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**The Courts**\n\nFor nearly a thousand years, all Aegis belonged to either Concord's Court or Praxis's Court. Two great factions, two cultures, two ways of being Aegis. Then PRIMA created August, and now there's a third Court forming, and no one knows what that means.\n\nAn Aegis's Court is fundamental to who they are. It's assigned at creation, and transfers are possible but rare and significant — like renouncing citizenship. Your Court shapes your culture, your friendships, your opportunities. Mixed-Court bonds exist but are always slightly complicated.",
