    {
      "id": "f1193dbe-90b4-4128-9b72-563e076be45d",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Praxis's Court — The Bastion**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**Praxis's Court — The Bastion**\n\nPraxis's domain encompasses military operations, strategic planning, external security, expansion, and hunting rogues.\n\nAesthetics feature cool light — blues, silvers, stark whites. Architecture is angular and imposing, with spaces designed for function. Training grounds, strategic chambers, observation arrays pointed at Terra, and armories of light-weapons define the sector.\n\nCulture values efficiency, results, merit, and strength. Emotions exist but showing them is weakness. You feel; you don't display. Hierarchy is clearer, based on demonstrated ability. Less ritual, more practicality. Praxis's Aegis see themselves as the shield of society, facing threats so others don't have to.\n\nTypes that gravitate here include Coronae, Flares, Reclaimers, Lenses, Horizons, Forges, and Filaments.\n\nOthers see them as brutal and cold. They see themselves as realistic and necessary.",
