    {
      "id": "b57ed9dd-3cdf-4f13-8471-470c1b3e53e8",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**August's Court — Unnamed**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**August's Court — Unnamed**\n\nAugust's Court is still being established. PRIMA has decreed that August will have her own Court, which means Aegis must be transferred from Concord or Praxis — politically explosive.\n\nWho gets assigned is contentious. Is it an honor, being chosen for PRIMA's newest project? Is it exile, removed from real power? Is it opportunity, ground floor of something new? Is it suspicious — why these Aegis specifically?\n\nThe sector is currently a strange mix of inherited spaces being reshaped. Some areas feel like Concord, some like Praxis, some like neither. August herself keeps rearranging things, experimenting. Her Aegis are making it up as they go.\n\nTypes that end up here include misfits who never fit either Court, unusually curious Aegis, those being punished or protected by transfer, Embers who are already outsiders, and anyone PRIMA specifically chooses.\n\nConcord's Court is wary — will August destabilize harmony? Praxis's Court is dismissive — a child playing at leadership. Both are watching very carefully.",
