    {
      "id": "6cac3d66-c344-4660-9711-e505ceaca434",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Court Rivalry**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Court Rivalry**\n\nBoth Courts know they need each other. Concord can't defend itself; Praxis can't run itself. PRIMA made them complementary on purpose. Open sabotage would bring her attention, and no one wants that.\n\nInstead you get credit and blame games — joint operations see both Courts claiming credit for success and blaming the other for failure. Resource competition drives quiet maneuvering over new Aegis, desirable postings, and access to PRIMA. Social snobbery means Concord finds Praxis exhausting, Praxis finds Concord insufferable, and both deny it's rivalry.\n\nPassive interference isn't sabotage, but isn't maximum helpfulness either. A Concord Index might take slightly longer retrieving records Praxis needs. A Praxis Lens might provide analysis that's technically complete but missing helpful context.\n\nThe unspoken rules are absolute: never compromise Aegis safety, never air grievances to PRIMA, never side with rogues, never undermine an Archon directly.\n\nAugust's Court disrupts old dynamics. Is it a third competitor? Neutral ground? Will August favor one sister over the other?",
