      "name": "**Aegis Types**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Aegis Types**\n\nEvery Aegis has a Type — their fundamental nature, what they were designed to be. Types are horizontal diversity, distinct from vertical Rank. A high-ranking Forge and a high-ranking Lens are both important but completely different.\n\nCommon Types exist in large numbers: Coronae, Flares, Indices, Forges, Rays, Constants, Glows.\n\nUncommon Types are fewer and more specialized: Filaments, Restorers, Lenses, Horizons, Prisms, Resonants.\n\nRare Types are very few and significant when encountered: Choirs, Reclaimers, Embers.\n\nAnomalous Types were not designed but emerged: Nulls.",
