    {
      "id": "273aac56-c3c0-4399-ad07-9d7b3ccb68f4",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The Beastfolk**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**The Beastfolk**\n\nThe beastfolk are a diverse group of sentient species that inhabit Terra. They are characterized by their animalistic features, such as fur, tails, and ears, though they are fully bipedal and capable of speech. The beastfolk are the dominant species on Terra, having adapted to the post-Rending world and developed their own societies and cultures. They are capable of using magic, having harnessed their SOULs to do so in the aftermath of the Rending. The beastfolk are generally more in tune with nature than humans, having a deep respect for the natural world and its balance. They are also more communal, valuing cooperation and mutual support over individualism.\n\nThe term \"beastfolk\" is largely a human designation — an outsider's flattening of enormous diversity. A lupine warrior from a frozen steppe would not naturally identify with a satyr merchant-priest from a river valley.\n\nThe major species of beastfolk include:\n\nLupines: A wolf-like species known for their strength and loyalty. They are often warriors.\n\nFelines: A cat-like species known for their agility and cunning. They are often hunters and scouts.\n\nElaphines: A deer-like species known for their endurance and wisdom. They are often merchants or handle logistics.\n\nSatyr: A goat-like species known for their unusually high magical skills and affinity with spellcasting. They are often magi or nobility, occupying the highest strata of society.",
