    {
      "id": "98a955fc-66d9-4316-8965-8d7df601ac55",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The Pavonines**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**The Pavonines**\n\nThe Pavonines are a unique avian beastfolk species found only on the islands of Aohane. Unlike the mammalian beastfolk found elsewhere on Terra, Pavonines are feathered, egg-laying, and fundamentally different in biology and culture. Their existence raises questions no one can fully answer — why here? Why only here?\n\nPavonines are humanoid in form like other beastfolk, but with distinct avian features. Their bodies are covered in feathers rather than fur, with coloration and patterning varying by individual and sex. Males have more vibrant, iridescent plumage and grow elaborate tail feathers from their lower back — the famous display that can be raised, fanned, and controlled. Females have subtler, elegant patterns. Their faces are more human-like than bird-like, but with sharp features and large eyes with unusual coloration. Their feet are taloned and bird-like.\n\nPavonines reproduce through eggs and experience seasonal molting — periods of vulnerability and renewal where feathers shed and regrow. New plumage is a social event, as the quality and patterns of feathers say something about health, status, and spiritual state.\n\nTheories about their origin abound. Some say the islands themselves are strange, with some Primordial resonance that allowed avian sentience to develop. Some scholars whisper the Pavonines were created by the United Empire — a theory they find deeply offensive. The Pavonines' own explanation is simply that Heaven chose them.",
