    {
      "id": "e5dc74a9-3195-4069-8dda-ca1892ea39eb",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The United Empire of Man**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**The United Empire of Man**\n\nThe United Empire of Man was not a continuation of ancient tradition but an ideological project — a specifically engineered pan-human culture built around shared human identity, nationalism, and a synthesis of pre-existing traditions. They were rabidly xenophobic and intent on ruling the entire Earth.\n\nThe Empire was hyper-rationalist, rejecting \"primitive\" traditions in favor of something deliberately new — clean, geometric, utilitarian. Beauty through function. They adopted celestial and light imagery because it fit their ideology of human supremacy: humans as the light of civilization, beastfolk as primitive darkness, illumination as truth revealed through science.\n\nThe Empire enforced a constructed lingua franca drawing from Greek for philosophy and high concepts, Latin for administration and practical matters, suppressing local tongues. They harvested symbols from every human culture, stripped context, and reassembled them into Imperial aesthetics. All of human history was rewritten as prologue to unification. Human supremacy became state religion — the SOUL, Passion, human uniqueness all weaponized into ideology. Beastfolk were not merely enemies but lesser beings who had stolen magic that rightfully belonged to humanity.\n\nThe ruling Imperial family experimented on themselves, seeking deeper connections to the Primordial and advantages over both beastfolk and common humans. These experiments had lasting effects on their bloodline.\n\nAfter the Rending, the constructed Imperial culture fractured. Different regions remembered different pieces, revived suppressed local traditions, or clung to Imperial identity with varying intensity.",
