    {
      "id": "2e554a0e-1be7-4065-baaa-e95e0e5d46c2",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The Solar Faith**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**The Solar Faith**\n\nThe dominant human religion holds that history moves in cycles, with each age ending in cataclysm. When the turning comes, humanity must unite or perish — the Empire exists to shield humanity from death during these transitions. The most recent turning was the Rending, which ended the Fourth Age and began the Fifth.\n\nThe faith is nominally unified under the Tonalpouhqui (Reader of Suns), a religious head based in Yolitzac. In practice, regional interpretations vary wildly, from the strict dualism of the Imperial Core to the ancestor veneration of the highlands. The Tonalpouhqui's authority is largely spiritual, possessing no army and often contested by rival claimants or powerful monarchs who install sympathetic candidates.\n\nThe human adoption of SOUL-magic is viewed differently across regions. Some see it as sacred obligation — feeding the age through sacrifice. Others view it as a stain, a desperate act that lowered humanity to beastfolk practices. This theological divide has never been resolved.",
