    {
      "id": "f138289f-f997-4712-b457-bd37b1105a05",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Tonal**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Tonal**\n\nPronounced \"toh-NAHL.\" Tonal is the central concept of the Solar Faith—it means something like \"sun-portion\" or \"heat-share,\" the vital warmth that animates all living things, given by the sun and owed back to it. Your tonal is your life-heat, your spiritual energy, your portion of the sun's gift that must eventually return.\n\n**Common usage:**\n\nWhen a mother holds a newborn: \"Strong tonal.\"\n\nWhen someone dies well, in sacrifice or battle: \"Their tonal rises.\"\n\nWhen someone is exhausted, sick, spiritually depleted: \"Low tonal\" or \"tonal-sick.\"\n\nWhen justifying sacrifice: \"The sun gave tonal; tonal returns.\"\n\nWhen greeting someone: \"Bright tonal\" — wishing them vitality.\n\nWhen mourning: \"The tonal is paid.\"\n\nThe phrase \"tonal-debt\" captures the entire sacrificial theology—you owe what you were given. The age requires feeding because every living thing carries borrowed heat.",
