    {
      "id": "ab0e5310-76a5-4891-8b76-a7f28e04e155",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Yolitzac**",
      "type": "location",
      "description": "**Yolitzac**\n\nYolitzac is the bureaucratic heart of human civilization, ruled by the Centeotl (One-Lord) from the partially preserved Imperial city of Tonallan (Place of the Sun). Yolitzac considers itself the true continuation of the United Empire, maintaining complex administrative systems and elaborate court protocols that have calcified over a thousand years.\n\nTheir religion is distinctly dualist, centered on the eternal struggle between sun and moon. The sun rises each dawn because humans believe it will — collective faith holds back the endless night. The moon is the defeated enemy that keeps returning, waiting for humanity's will to falter. One day, if humanity disbelieved too much or gave up, the moon might win, leading to a neverending night.\n\nPractices include dawn vigils, confession of doubts, and treating despair as spiritually dangerous. Lunar eclipses are days of crisis and mass ritual.\n\nThe nobility performs elaborate rituals of status, and titles often mask true functions. The Xochihua (Flower Handler), for instance — ostensibly responsible for court artistic arrangements — is actually the crown's chief assassin and operative.\n\nYolitzac views its neighbors with formal contempt, seeing itself as civilization surrounded by decay. Foreign diplomats face elaborate protocols designed to reinforce their inferior status.",
