    {
      "id": "519cb143-a00c-4cc2-9a92-4db6082bb8e8",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Yolica**",
      "type": "location",
      "description": "**Yolica**\n\nYolica is a region of multiple kingdoms in the western heartland sharing traditions where magic is understood as \"feeding the age\" — each SOUL-bargain sustains the current cycle. Refusal to use magic when needed may be the greater transgression.\n\n**Cuauhtemoc (Eagle Descending)** — A martial kingdom where warrior-mages form the elite. Battle-sacrifice feeds the age. Rivals Yolitzac's claim to Imperial heritage.\n\n**Xochimilca (Place of Flower Fields)** — The agricultural heartland that feeds much of the continent. Priesthood focused on cycles, planting, and growth. Their magic is tied to fertility and seasons — less dramatic but deeply rooted. Considered \"soft\" by neighbors, but controls the food supply.\n\n**Micteca (Place of the Dead)** — A smaller state built around a massive Primordial access point, likely a vast cave system. Specialist death-priests negotiate with ancestors and tend to the dying. Other states find them unsettling but necessary, sending important dead here for proper rites.",
