    {
      "id": "c1fd6fa6-e85d-43c8-9cb8-ab60fa26b328",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Oliken**",
      "type": "location",
      "description": "**Oliken**\n\nOliken is not a unified region but a collection of rival city-states in the southern lowlands sharing cultural roots. Alliances shift constantly, and warfare between cities is common if ritualized.\n\nThe Hero Twins prophecy is central here — two figures who will descend to the Primordial and outwit death itself. Multiple cities claim the Twins will emerge from their sacred site.\n\n**Kanhul (Four Waters)** — Built around sacred cenotes that serve as access points to the Primordial. Powerful and arrogant, certain of their prophetic importance.\n\n**Yaxchilan (Green Stones)** — Wealthy from jade trade, more mercantile in character. Religious practice is elaborate but transactional, systematized. Rivals with Kanhul.\n\n**Oxwitza (Three Hills)** — An older, declining city claiming the most ancient traditions. Other cities raid their scholars and libraries. Currently a resentful client state of Kanhul.\n\n**Lakamtun (Stacked Stones)** — A fortress city controlling key mountain passes into the highlands. More martial, less refined. Hire out soldiers, occasionally even to beastfolk — considered distasteful by other Oliken cities.",
