    {
      "id": "f590a04c-4210-45ca-a4d7-42797ccc5801",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Yullqa**",
      "type": "location",
      "description": "**Yullqa**\n\nYullqa is not a kingdom but a confederation of communities in the eastern highlands bound by reciprocity. Traditions here emphasize balanced exchange — ayni — as cosmic law. The SOUL-bargain is not damage but fair trade with the universe.\n\nAncestor veneration is central. The Primordial is not abstract theology — it is where grandmother went, and you maintain relationship with her through offerings and consultation.\n\n**The Qullqamarka (The Silver Union)** — The network itself rather than a state. Communities at different altitudes specialize: lowland cotton for highland wool, valley maize for mountain potatoes. Refusal to participate in exchange is the gravest social offense.\n\n**Willkakuti (Return of the Sacred)** — The closest thing to a capital, a high-altitude religious center where the most important ancestors are preserved. A pilgrimage site whose priests do not rule but whose words carry enormous weight.\n\n**The Qhapaq Ñan (The Great Road)** — A network of roads and way-stations maintained collectively, predating even the Empire. Semi-sacred; attacking travelers on the road is taboo across the highlands.",
