    {
      "id": "3de660cb-456f-4553-9994-b48b59fb9654",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Yolca**",
      "type": "location",
      "description": "**Yolca**\n\nYolca encompasses the coastal reaches, the most heterodox region, shaped by trade and contact with outsiders.\n\n**Chalatica (Place of Sea-Mouths)** — A republic governed by merchant families across multiple ports. Beastfolk traders are welcome here, unlike most human territories. Syncretic religion absorbs foreign practices readily. Other humans see them as morally compromised; they see others as provincial.\n\n**The Raft-Cities** — Floating communities following fishing and trade routes rather than claiming land. Extremely heterodox religiously, possibly incorporating beastfolk beliefs. Looked down upon but economically useful. May have developed unique sea-based magical traditions.",
