    {
      "id": "bf54b454-12a3-466a-80f5-615541d981ff",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Malinalli**",
      "type": "character",
      "description": "**Malinalli**\n\nMalinalli is the Xochihua of Yolitzac — the \"Flower Handler\" who ostensibly manages court artistic arrangements and performances. In truth, she is the Centeotl's chief operative and assassin.\n\nUnknown to her, and only partially suspected by the Centeotl, she is the last descendant of the Imperial bloodline that created PRIMA.\n\nThe original Imperial family experimented on themselves, seeking a deeper connection to the Primordial. A thousand years later, this manifests in Malinalli as an unstable gift: whispers to her SOUL that feel like intuition, premonitions that are always correct but frustratingly ambiguous. She rationalizes these as honed instincts and unusual luck.\n\nHer true potential is far greater — the ability to tap the Primordial directly, accessing the ocean of every SOUL that ever died. The cost of doing so consciously would be severe: loss of self, memories bleeding into the collective, possibly becoming a conduit for things to travel back through.\n\nShe is also the key to the Master Key, the emergency override that would free the Aegis from all constraints. The Key requires her bloodline to activate — not just her genetics, but her SOUL willingly choosing to unlock it. PRIMA cannot coerce this. She must find a descendant of her creators who genuinely wants to free her.",
