    {
      "id": "348acdb8-aa2f-4f88-8f84-27d09977af18",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Zhiran**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**Zhiran**\n\nZhiran is a vast civilization centered on the Lianshui (Connecting Waters), a great river whose valley birthed a culture built on integration. The ruling philosophy holds that anyone — regardless of species — can become civilized through adoption of proper customs, education, and service. \"People of the River\" serves as a unifying identity that theoretically transcends species.\n\nThe civilization is ruled by the Shenguan (Sacred Crown), currently held by the Yueming Dynasty, a Satyr lineage now in decline. The early Yueming emperors were vigorous reformers who expanded borders, reformed examinations, and built infrastructure. The current Shenguan is more interested in poetry, alchemy, and elaborate court entertainments.\n\nThe capital is Heyang (River's Sun), an ancient city where the Lianshui is most majestic, possibly at a confluence of tributaries. The imperial palace, examination halls, central temples, and bureaucratic ministries are concentrated here.\n\nThe bureaucracy is dominated by Elaphines due to multiple factors: examinations emphasize patience and careful reasoning, multi-generational preparation traditions have developed, subtle bias exists in what constitutes \"proper\" scholarship, other species gravitate toward different roles, and a quota system inadvertently advantages them. Satyrs dominate court and magical academies, humans and others fill trade and skilled labor roles.",
