    {
      "id": "a97a65a7-7934-48a4-92fb-e33e57173f52",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Schools and Debates of Heliushuo**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Schools and Debates of Heliushuo**\n\nThe Cultivation School holds that self-discipline refines the SOUL over decades — slow, steady, safe. This is orthodox teaching, emphasized in examinations.\n\nThe Passion Heresy argues that intense Passion — burning bright — can achieve in moments what cultivation takes years to reach. Orthodox scholars condemn this as dangerous, Imperial-adjacent thinking. But the results are undeniable when it works.\n\nThe Barbarian Question asks whether Göran and Drakhar are truly imbalanced, or have achieved a different harmony that Zhiran refuses to recognize. Some border scholars who have studied these peoples suggest uncomfortable possibilities.\n\nThe Human Question asks what the United Empire was and what it means for humans today. Views range from orthodox shame to heretical pride, with most humans navigating somewhere uncomfortably between. Some see the Empire as humanity's great sin, others as proof of human potential, others as stolen birthright absorbed into Zhiran's framework.",
