    {
      "id": "10b028c3-6284-43e1-870c-08874602e050",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Zhiran Historical Figures**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Zhiran Historical Figures**\n\n**Liuhan the Unifier** — Semi-legendary first ruler who established the integration philosophy. Species debated by scholars; everyone claims him. May have been a coalition rather than one person, but the myth says otherwise.\n\n**The Five Sages** — One of each species, who supposedly codified Heliushuo. Convenient propaganda, but their attributed writings form the examination canon.\n\n**The Tianshu Dynasty** — Elaphine rulers, famous for building the great walls and establishing the examination system. Fell to internal corruption.\n\n**The Zhangling Dynasty** — Human rulers, controversial. Expanded Zhiran's borders significantly but also introduced \"Passion-cultivation\" heresies. Orthodox scholars blame them for legitimizing dangerous practices. Fell when the Mandate clearly passed — three years of drought followed by Göran invasion.\n\n**The Baiyue Dynasty** — Feline rulers, the only time that species held the throne. Brief but militarily glorious, pushed Drakhar back into the deepest mountains. Fell to succession crisis when the empress died without clear heir.\n\n**General Yueming Zhao** — Founded current dynasty three centuries ago by \"restoring order\" after the Baiyue collapse. A Satyr military man, not a scholar — which made him effective but always slightly illegitimate in orthodox eyes.\n\n**Shenguan Yueming Enlai** — Third emperor, considered the dynasty's peak. Reformed examinations, built canals, patronized arts. The current court tries to imitate his style without his substance.",
