    {
      "id": "d3d5f1ec-dfd6-48b9-8c4a-fc8d73cdb4f3",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Zhiran Military**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**Zhiran Military**\n\nThe conscript system (Bingyi) requires every household to owe labor to the state — this can be fulfilled through infrastructure work, but border households often fulfill it through military service. In theory, this creates massive armies when needed. In practice, training is minimal, equipment is locally supplied and inconsistent, and officers are either examination-passed bureaucrats who know nothing of war or hereditary military families whom the court distrusts.\n\nSpecies roles in the military follow predictable patterns. Elaphines handle quartermasters, logistics, and siege engineering. Satyrs serve as battle-mages, officers, and strategists. Lupines serve as cavalry, shock troops, and scouts — \"civilized\" Lupines are disproportionately military, as it is a respected path to integration. Felines serve as skirmishers, spies, and irregular warfare specialists — rare, mistrusted, but effective. Humans serve as infantry, the bulk of conscript armies, their Passion making them dangerous in desperate moments but unreliable in discipline.\n\nThe Yueming court has not fought a real war in generations. Military budgets have been raided for court entertainments, generals are chosen for political loyalty rather than competence, and border commanders know the rot but cannot fix it from below.",
