    {
      "id": "ae7f25a2-cd6e-4878-a527-d526024dd973",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Zhiran Magic**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Zhiran Magic**\n\nTemple Magic (Miaoshu) is practiced primarily through religious institutions. Temples to Heaven, the River, and ancestors maintain trained priests who perform agricultural rituals, maintain spiritual balance in communities, heal the sick through SOUL-mending, communicate with ancestors, and consecrate important events.\n\nMilitary applications (Zhanshu) include battlefield healing, morale rituals strengthening soldiers' resolve, weather influence such as fog to cover movements, warding to protect camps, and divination to read enemy movements.\n\nBorder temples quietly teach techniques that would make heartland scholars uncomfortable — ways to burn brighter temporarily, accepting SOUL-damage for immediate power. The justification: defending Zhiran's harmony is itself harmonious. This is where the \"Passion Heresy\" lives in practice.",
