    {
      "id": "3bc2e564-6892-4713-b19d-2f98bfbdc1d3",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Beifang**",
      "type": "location",
      "description": "**Beifang**\n\nBeifang (Northern Marches) faces Göran. Flat terrain gradually transitions to steppe. Great walls, garrison towns, and military culture define the region despite the dynasty's neglect.\n\nMajor cities include Tiecheng (Iron City, the great fortress-city anchoring northern defenses) and Langfang (Wolf Defense, a garrison town with significant \"civilized\" Lupine population serving as scouts and cavalry).\n\nMore Lupines live here than anywhere else in Zhiran — those who have rejected Göran's ways or been exiled. The military has been underfunded for decades, and local commanders have started making private arrangements with border traders. If Göran unifies, this region knows it will burn first.",
      "hiddenInfo": null,
