    {
      "id": "065b500b-4178-4a81-8191-76f00e757e2a",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Nanhai**",
      "type": "location",
      "description": "**Nanhai**\n\nNanhai (Southern Coasts) is mercantile, cosmopolitan, wealthy, and religiously flexible.\n\nMajor cities include Zhugang (Pearl Harbor, the largest port), Bailang (White Wave, a shipbuilding center), and Haimen (Sea Gate, closest port to the Sanzhou islands).\n\nThe autonomous Sanzhou (Three Islands) archipelago is nominally under Nanhai's administration. The largest island has a proper Zhiran governor; the smaller two are effectively independent fishing and trading communities, heavily human with traditions that look more like overseas practices than proper Heliushuo.\n\nHuman plurality exists in several port cities, with significant overseas trader populations. Wealthy merchants buy examination passes for less-capable children. Orthodox scholars are horrified; the court is paid off.",
