    {
      "id": "1fcc0aa5-1ec2-48ae-a8be-8a6ea7213a92",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Dongyuan**",
      "type": "location",
      "description": "**Dongyuan**\n\nDongyuan (Eastern Reaches) is the most recently absorbed region, perhaps only a few centuries under Zhiran rule. Fertile plains, rice cultivation, and distinct local identity define it.\n\nMajor cities include Donglin (Eastern Forest, the regional capital where Zhiran administration meets local tradition) and Renzhou (Human Prefecture, a majority-human city with special administrative status).\n\nHigher human percentage exists here than anywhere except Nanhai ports. The original terms of submission guaranteed certain rights that the heartland periodically tries to erode. Local humans are not sure if they are \"Zhiran humans\" or \"Dongyuan people who happen to be human.\"",
