    {
      "id": "734f19d4-7b7b-4353-966f-0bd12dc642e4",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Göran**",
      "type": "location",
      "description": "**Göran**\n\nGöran is the vast steppe homeland of the Lupines, lying beyond Zhiran's northern borders. The Lupines here rejected integration, maintaining single-species society built around pack hierarchy scaled to enormous size.\n\nThe steppe is infinite in their philosophy. It does not hold your dead; it releases them. When a Lupine dies, their SOUL runs with the eternal wind, joins the great hunt across the sky. They do not guard territory because no territory is sacred — the movement is sacred. To settle is to die spiritually.\n\nSocial structure follows pack hierarchy: alpha to pack, pack to clan, clan to horde, horde to khan. When a great khan rises, unification is almost automatic. The structure exists; it only needs someone strong enough to sit at the top. This has happened multiple times in history, and Zhiran has nearly fallen to Lupine hordes before.\n\nGöran Lupines ride qilin-like creatures — antlered, scaled, and fast — bred for war and steppe travel. Their raids are seasonal, coming when the grass is good and their herds are strong. Zhiran's great walls and border forts exist primarily for them.\n\nThey view the integrated river-folk as mongrels who abandoned their true nature. To them, species purity is strength. They also hate the Felines of Drakhar with ancient fury — the two barbarian peoples do not ally against Zhiran, which is partly why the river civilization has survived.",
      "hiddenInfo": null,
      "aliases": [
        "**Göran**"
