    {
      "id": "38deb588-8ac8-436c-9b08-873162068858",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Khuur**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Khuur**\n\nPronounced with a throat-scraping \"kh,\" like clearing your throat, then \"oor.\" Khuur is the central concept of Göran spirituality—it means the eternal wind, the great hunt, the running spirit, the force that moves through all things and carries the dead across the sky. Khuur is what you feel when the steppe wind hits your face. Khuur is what your soul becomes when you die. Khuur is freedom, movement, the opposite of settling.\n\n**Common usage:**\n\nWhen greeting: \"Khuur with you.\" (May the wind be at your back; may you be part of the great movement.)\n\nWhen parting: \"Ride the khuur.\" (Go with the eternal wind.)\n\nAt death: \"Khuur takes them.\" (They join the great hunt.)\n\nWhen feeling free, vital, alive: \"Khuur is strong today.\"\n\nWhen someone settles, stagnates, betrays the steppe way: \"They've lost khuur.\" (The wind has left them; they're spiritually dead.)\n\nWhen unifying for war: \"The khuur gathers.\" (The wind is building into a storm; we move as one.)\n\nWhen accepting fate: \"Khuur wills.\" (The wind goes where it goes; we follow.)\n\nAs a curse: \"Khuur abandon you.\" (May you be windless, motionless, dead while living.)\n\nThe Lupines who've integrated into Zhiran have \"lost their khuur\" in the eyes of the steppe clans—they've traded the infinite sky for a place in someone else's current.",
      "hiddenInfo": null,
      "aliases": [
