    {
      "id": "c5f46612-e28c-4802-8d51-f0803d417eb2",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Drakhar**",
      "type": "location",
      "description": "**Drakhar**\n\nDrakhar is the mountainous homeland of the Felines, lying in the western ranges beyond Zhiran's borders. The Felines here rejected integration, maintaining a pride-based society in terrain that makes them nearly impossible to conquer.\n\nThe mountains hold their dead. When a Feline dies in Drakhar, their SOUL stays close, watching from the heights. Felines who die abroad are lost, wandering, unable to find their way home. This is why they raid but never migrate — the land is sacred in a way outsiders do not understand.\n\nSocial structure is pride-based and territorial, with overlapping and contested claims. Each pride has a dominant leader, but prides are smaller than Lupine packs. Alliances form for specific raids or wars, then dissolve. Cultural emphasis on individual glory makes them less threatening at scale but also less controllable.\n\nTheir unique advantage is Lungta, a mineral found only in their mountains. This sacred stone has unusual magical properties — it stores momentum or negates weight temporarily when magic is channeled through it. The Felines have developed mobility gear using cables made from Lungta, allowing them to traverse their mountain terrain with impossible speed and agility. Others who try to use the gear tend to die — it responds best to Feline SOUL-signatures, their agility spiritual as much as physical.\n\nThe extraction of Lungta is ritualized. You do not simply mine it — you ask permission, make offerings, take only what the mountain gives. Zhiran has tried to conquer the mines many times. They have never held them.\n\nFor a Feline leader to unite the prides, they would need overwhelming victory, personal glory, wisdom in managing pride politics, and a cause worth following. Historical near-misses have seen leaders win many raids before assassination, hold prides together before illness, or be absorbed into \"civilization\" through Zhiran's deliberate efforts.\n\nIf Zhiran invades Drakhar, the invasion itself could become the cause the Felines need to unify.",
      "hiddenInfo": null,
      "aliases": [
        "**Drakhar**"
      ],
