    {
      "id": "0cf1c938-e172-4de4-a690-bf2f79997e11",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Lungta**",
      "type": "item",
      "description": "**Lungta**\n\nLungta is both the sacred mineral found only in Drakhar's mountains and the broader spiritual concept it embodies—the connection between the living and the dead who dwell in the peaks, the vertical axis that connects earth to height to the souls of ancestors watching from above. More than a resource, lungta represents everything the Felines hold sacred about their homeland.\n\nThe mineral itself has unusual magical properties—it stores momentum or negates weight temporarily when magic is channeled through it. The Felines have developed mobility gear using cables made from lungta, allowing them to traverse their mountain terrain with impossible speed and agility. The gear responds best to Feline SOUL-signatures; outsiders who try to use it tend to die.\n\n**Common usage:**\n\nWhen blessing someone: \"Lungta with you.\" (May the mountain's gift be yours; may the ancestors favor you.)\n\nWhen claiming something earned: \"My lungta.\" (What I've achieved through my own climbing.)\n\nWhen someone dies in Drakhar: \"Lungta holds them.\" (The mountain receives their soul.)\n\nWhen someone dies abroad: \"Lost to lungta.\" (Their soul wanders, unable to find the heights.)\n\nWhen praising excellence: \"High lungta.\" (They've climbed far; the ancestors see them.)\n\nWhen insulting: \"No lungta.\" (Unblessed, unconnected, flatlander in spirit.)\n\nWhen the gear works, when a climb succeeds: \"Lungta guides.\"\n\nWhen facing danger: \"Trust the lungta.\" (The mountain will provide; the ancestors watch.)\n\nThe Felines who've integrated into Zhiran have \"abandoned their lungta\"—they've left the mountains that hold their dead and can never return to their proper height.",
