    {
      "id": "1abd703b-5cc0-45a1-a8d8-9066f76a3680",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Goryun**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**Goryun**\n\nGoryun is a human-majority nation occupying a defensible peninsula extending from the Zhiran continent. It proves that humans can build sophisticated civilization without being \"civilized\" by beastfolk and without clinging to Imperial legacy.\n\nThe peninsula's humans predate the United Empire's expansion. When Imperial forces arrived, the mountainous northern border made conquest costly. The Empire established tribute relationships and coastal trading posts but never fully integrated the interior. During the Rending, those footholds collapsed, leaving the peninsular humans damaged but not destroyed.\n\nCrucially, small beastfolk populations — primarily Elaphines in the valleys and some Felines in the eastern mountains — had coexisted with the humans for generations. When post-Rending chaos brought raiders, humans and beastfolk chose cooperation over conflict. The Compact of Three Fires established mutual defense and respect: humans held political dominance due to numbers, but beastfolk were partners with protected rights, not subjects.\n\nGeographic luck sealed their survival. The northern mountains channel any invasion into a few passes, easily defended. By the time Zhiran consolidated, Goryun was too established to conquer cheaply.",
