      "id": "cafd4425-9334-4169-9a40-3d153c1a38b5",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Goryun Government**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**Goryun Government**\n\nThe nation is ruled by the Gun (Lord), rejecting grander Imperial titles. The capital is Samhwa (Three Fires), named for the founding Compact. The city sits in the western plains backed against mountains — ancient, grand but not ostentatious, containing the Three Fires Temple where the original flames are still maintained.\n\nThe Compact Assembly ensures beastfolk voices are heard in governance. Human nobles dominate numerically, but beastfolk votes carry extra weight on matters affecting their communities. This is not Zhiran's \"we'll civilize you\" integration — it is negotiated partnership between peoples who chose each other.\n\nGoryun adopted examination systems from Zhiran but modified them to emphasize their own philosophy. The military track is more prestigious than in Zhiran.",
