    {
      "id": "24de2b24-e21f-40c3-82ee-d2412dbabb2d",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Aohane Government**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**Aohane Government**\n\nThe nation is ruled by the Tenkaze (Heaven's Wind), a title that may pass to either sex. Succession is not strictly hereditary — the winds \"choose\" somehow, through omens, trials, or the previous ruler's designation.\n\nThe capital is Kumotori (Cloud-Taker), an ancient city built into a volcanic mountain's slopes, so high that clouds drift through its streets. Architecture is vertical — terraces, towers, and bridges spanning chasms, built for a people comfortable with heights. The lowest levels are ruins no one fully understands. Wind channels design the city so breezes flow in specific patterns. Light gardens catch and reflect sunlight through crystal and water. The Pinnacle holds the Tenkaze's palace at the highest point, above the cloud line on clear days.",
