    {
      "id": "308a361b-618f-4828-ae9d-6cc854697e66",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Aohane Philosophy**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Aohane Philosophy**\n\nThe Pavonines adopted elements of Heliushuo but developed their own interpretation. The Five Natures does not apply to them — they are outside the mammalian framework and know it. Some Pavonine philosophers have proposed they represent a sixth nature; others reject the entire system as provincial.\n\nDisplay as virtue distinguishes them from Zhiran's emphasis on restraint. Aohane culture values beauty, splendor, and visible excellence. Hiding your gifts is almost shameful.\n\nMolting as renewal centers their spirituality on cycles of shedding and regrowth. The SOUL is not just cultivated; it is periodically remade.",
