    {
      "id": "52ab0228-0b51-45cb-bbb1-afa3f6d88db8",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Aohane Magic**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Aohane Magic**\n\nThe Pavonines specialize in wind and light magic, both intangible forces that reflect their nature.\n\nWind Magic (Fūjutsu) includes reading winds for prophecy and navigation — this is why their sailors can cross seas that wreck foreign ships. They can call or calm storms for defense, send whispers on the wind across vast distances, create cutting gales for combat, and at highest mastery achieve brief personal flight — not sustained, but miraculous leaps and glides.\n\nLight Magic (Kōjutsu) includes illusion and display, bending light for concealment and misdirection, capturing light in objects so their lacquerware and silk seem to glow from within, reading sun and stars for divination, and prismatic bursts for combat.\n\nBoth magics are beautiful, ephemeral, impossible to pin down. Mammals find it unsettling. The Pavonines say: that is the point. You cannot hold wind. You cannot catch light. And you cannot conquer Aohane.",
