    {
      "id": "b84a32e6-450d-4ca2-b5df-a9a5208d64e3",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Aohane Isolationism**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Aohane Isolationism**\n\nAohane trades but carefully. They permit visitors but controlled. They do not expand or interfere.\n\nThey are self-sufficient — the islands provide what they need. They see themselves as peers to Zhiran, not students. They guard secrets about their unique nature, their magic, their sacred sites. Early contact with the mainland may have gone badly, teaching them to keep distance.\n\nWhat outsiders know: Aohane exists and trades beautiful goods, they are bird-people, their islands are deadly to approach without permission, their magic is different and hard to counter, no one has successfully invaded them, and they do not seem interested in anyone else's affairs.\n\nWhat outsiders do not know: how their society actually functions, what happens in Kumotori, why they are the only avian beastfolk, what their deepest magic can really do, or what they want.",
