    {
      "id": "cafe7508-0264-4771-8584-e3a3c4644c9c",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Relations in the Zhiran Sphere**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Relations in the Zhiran Sphere**\n\nZhiran sees Goryun as a wayward cousin who should acknowledge cultural superiority, and Aohane as civilized but unsettling peers. Goryun sees Zhiran as an overbearing neighbor with delusions of universal truth. Aohane sees both as useful but keeps distance.\n\nGoryun and Aohane share warmer relations as fellow independent nations who have resisted Zhiran absorption. Trade flows between them through Goryun's southern ports, with mutual respect but no deep entanglement.\n\nZhiran sees both Göran and Drakhar as barbarians who have severed themselves from cosmic harmony. The barbarian peoples hate each other as much as they hate the river civilization, which is partly why Zhiran survives.\n\nYolcentla has almost no contact with this sphere — too distant for regular trade, no shared identity despite common humanity. Goryun humans are vaguely aware of \"the human continent\" where their distant cousins built something different.",
