    {
      "id": "0e9a911a-8bbb-4b7f-959e-b3e72eca7e7d",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The Tieravel Continent**",
      "type": "location",
      "description": "**The Tieravel Continent**\n\nTieravel (Old Tongue: \"First Earth\") is the third major continent of Terra and the ancient homeland of all beastfolk. This is where beastfolk began — not just historically, but spiritually and magically. The very first beastfolk drew breath here, lived here, died here. Their SOULs sank into this soil. Then their children's SOULs. Then their children's children's. For uncounted millennia before humans even existed as a distinct species, beastfolk walked this land.\n\nThe result: the Primordial runs closer to the surface here than anywhere else on Terra. Every sacred grove, every standing stone circle, every mountain shrine sits atop layers upon layers of accumulated ancestral memory. Magic here is easier, more intuitive, but also more dangerous. The dead have opinions.\n\nThe continent is shaped roughly like a crescent moon, with a vast inner sea at its heart. This geography creates a natural division between two cultural spheres: the Thalassic sphere of human city-states around the warm inner sea, and the Brythonic sphere of beastfolk clans and kingdoms in the misty outer reaches. The two spheres meet along a contested middle band of river valleys, mountain passes, and coastal marchlands where cultures clash, blend, and trade.",
