    {
      "id": "63e8c87d-73ae-4334-afb2-a64bf2d6babc",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The Great Diaspora**",
      "type": "event",
      "description": "**The Great Diaspora**\n\nAt some point in prehistory — the exact timeline is debated — beastfolk began migrating outward from Tieravel.\n\nThe Northern Migration brought Lupines across land bridges or ice sheets to what would become Göran. They adapted to the steppe, developed their pack-horde structure, and eventually forgot they had ever lived anywhere else. The eternal wind became their home; the idea that land could be sacred seemed absurd.\n\nThe Western Migration brought Felines across mountain ranges to what would become Drakhar. They found new peaks to claim, new valleys to guard. Their belief that the mountains hold their dead is a continuation of the Old Law, adapted to new territory — but they have been away so long that Tieravel Felines consider them cousins, not kin.\n\nThe Eastern Migration brought mixed populations across narrow seas to what would become the Zhiran continent. These beastfolk integrated with the humans they found there, eventually developing Heliushuo's philosophy of harmony. They are the most changed — they have accepted that identity does not require the homeland.\n\nThe Satyrs largely stayed. They have always had the strongest connection to the Primordial, and leaving the land where that connection runs deepest felt like spiritual suicide. This is why Satyrs are rarer outside Tieravel and why they occupy the highest magical positions — they are the keepers of the oldest traditions.",
