    {
      "id": "f41e7686-7738-4d70-9605-c643f9ed3b48",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Tieravel Magic**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Tieravel Magic**\n\nThe ancient homeland's unique Primordial density makes geomantic magic stronger here than anywhere else on Terra — but also more complex.\n\nIn Zhiran, the Primordial is like a deep river: accessible but requiring skill to reach. In Yolcentla, it is like a well: you bargain with it, draw from it, pay the price. In Göran and Drakhar, it is like wind or stone: elemental, tied to specific aspects.\n\nIn Tieravel, the Primordial is an ocean that laps at your feet. The accumulated SOULs of countless generations create a density of spiritual presence that is almost overwhelming. Apprentice mages from other continents who visit often have to acclimatize — the noise of ancestral presence can drive the unprepared mad.\n\nThis also means that the dead are more present here. Not as ghosts exactly, but as influences. Patterns of thought that echo through generations. Emotional residue that colors entire regions. A battlefield from ten thousand years ago might still feel like despair. A sacred grove where lovers met for centuries might still feel like joy.\n\nHuman mages find this deeply unsettling. Their Hearth Flame tradition is about collective living SOULs resonating together. The idea that dead SOULs might have opinions, might influence the present, feels like necromancy to them.",
