    {
      "id": "09b0762b-6532-4350-86dc-25d405349c02",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The Imperial Colonization**",
      "type": "event",
      "description": "**The Imperial Colonization**\n\nThe human presence on Tieravel did not begin with refugees — it began with conquest.\n\nBefore the Rending, the United Empire of Man was a global hegemon. Tonallan was its capital, but Imperial colonies stretched across Terra. Tieravel, the ancient homeland of the beastfolk, was a primary target. The Empire established naval bases, administrative centers, and garrison cities around the inner sea. At the height of Imperial power, humans controlled most of the continent — the beastfolk pushed to the margins, confined to highlands, deep forests, and places too difficult to hold.\n\nThe Great Library of Antheion? Imperial colonial archives. The Lucian Arsenal? Built on Imperial drydocks. The Salt Road through Skaros? Imperial military supply routes. Every major Thalassic city stands on foundations the Empire laid.\n\nThe beastfolk remember this. The humans have... conveniently forgotten.",
