    {
      "id": "ac445072-44a9-4c92-a892-aa73c441ecd7",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The Beasttide**",
      "type": "event",
      "description": "**The Beasttide**\n\nWhen the Rending struck, everything changed in a single catastrophic moment.\n\nImperial technology died. Guns became useless metal. Vehicles stopped. Communications severed. Supply lines to Tonallan collapsed. The colonial armies — which had conquered through technological supremacy — suddenly had nothing but swords and confusion.\n\nAnd the beastfolk had magic.\n\nIn the aftermath of the Rending, the beastfolk discovered how to harness their SOULs. The humans, cut off from Imperial support and surrounded by enemies who now wielded supernatural power, faced extermination.\n\nThe Beasttide was not a war — it was a reckoning. Beastfolk rose up everywhere at once. Colonial cities burned. Garrisons were overrun. A thousand years of occupation undone in a generation. The beastfolk still sing of this time: the liberation, the heroes who broke the Imperial yoke, the night the harbor of Lucia lit up the sky for three days when the Saltraeth burned the colonial fleet.\n\nThe humans remember it differently — when they remember it at all. The Beasttide is trauma buried deep. Their histories skip from \"the great Empire\" to \"the founding of our noble cities\" with a haze in between. If you dig in the archives, you find casualty lists that don't make sense unless the population halved. Letters begging Tonallan for rescue that never came. A map showing forty-seven Imperial colonies on Tieravel.\n\nEight survived.",
