    {
      "id": "7a103cb2-7279-4cf2-84a5-764596caeb5b",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Humans as Colonizers**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Humans as Colonizers**\n\nThe human presence on Tieravel is not recent. It is ancient — as ancient as the Empire's ambition. But the humans are not *from* here. Their dead do not rest in this soil going back millennia. Their gwraidd is elsewhere, or nowhere.\n\nThis creates a fundamental tension with no easy resolution. The humans see themselves as survivors of tragedy, heirs to civilization, builders who have lived here for a thousand years. The beastfolk see them as colonizers who almost got what they deserved — and who still occupy stolen land.\n\nDifferent groups tell different stories about what happened. But the beastfolk remember. The land remembers. The ancestors remember.",
