    {
      "id": "0c84e9bc-7da8-4911-8962-2afbfaabd878",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Lucia**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**Lucia**\n\nLucia is the great maritime power of the inner sea, its Flame kindled on a defensible peninsula where the colonial naval base once stood. When the Beasttide came, Lucia's position — surrounded by water on three sides — and its access to ships made it one of the few colonies that could be held. The Lucian Arsenal, pride of the Thalassic world, is built directly on Imperial drydocks.\n\nThe nation is governed by an elected Doge who rules for life, chosen by a council of merchant families. The position carries enormous prestige but limited formal power — the great families balance each other through constant negotiation.\n\nLucians venerate the Navigator Stars, a syncretic faith that absorbed sailor superstitions from every port. Their priests are astrologers and cartographers who read fate in celestial movements. The faith quietly incorporates elements borrowed from beastfolk traditions — Lucia has always been practical about such things.\n\nLucia is the most beastfolk-tolerant human state in the Thalassic sphere. Their port quarters have permanent Elaphine merchant colonies, and Lucian law recognizes beastfolk contracts. Other human states consider them morally compromised; Lucia considers others provincial. The Saltraeth raid Lucian shipping regularly — this is simply the cost of doing business in the inner sea.\n\nLucia's founding myth involves desperate refugees who found empty shores and built civilization from nothing. The beastfolk remember the truth: a colonial naval base that held through the Beasttide because the Saltraeth couldn't breach its harbor chains before the Flame kindled. The debt has never been acknowledged.\n\n**Population: 5-7 million.** The capital city holds roughly 300,000-400,000.",
