    {
      "id": "00d1f46c-19f5-4425-b67e-a8dfbc429edd",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Antheion**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**Antheion**\n\nAntheion is the oldest and largest human civilization on the inner sea, built around the great river delta that served as the Imperial provincial capital. The Great Library — originally the colonial administrative archives — holds more pre-Rending knowledge than anywhere else on Terra. Scholars pilgrim here to study texts that exist nowhere else. Beastfolk historians note bitterly that many of these documents detail the conquest of their ancestors.\n\nAntheion's Flame is the oldest in the Thalassic sphere, kindled in the earliest days of the Beasttide. Some claim it was the *first* Flame, though Archepyros disputes this. What is certain: Antheion's Flame has burned for a thousand years without interruption. No one knows what it could do at full power. No one wants to find out.\n\nThe nation is ruled by Philosopher-Kings, a council of scholar-mages who theoretically govern through wisdom. In practice, factional politics between philosophical schools determines policy, with different academies representing different interpretations of the Civic Flame tradition.\n\nThe river delta is phenomenally fertile, making Antheion the breadbasket of the Thalassic sphere. They feed half the human cities and know it, using grain as a diplomatic weapon when necessary. The irony is not lost on anyone: Antheion feeds the humans with land taken from the beastfolk, using agricultural techniques developed over millennia by the peoples they displaced.\n\n**Population: 9-11 million.** The largest human nation. The capital city holds roughly 400,000-500,000.",
