    {
      "id": "2b6bf9df-a4a1-4cd6-8a40-57c95e263c08",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Kartheia**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**Kartheia**\n\nKartheia is a confederation of city-states on the western inner sea coast, founded as Lucian colonies after the Beasttide. This makes them young by Thalassic standards — their Flames are only six centuries old, and they feel the weakness keenly.\n\nEach city is governed by an Assembly — direct democracy among citizens, though slaves and foreigners do not count. This makes them chaotic but fierce; their armies fight for their own cities, not for pay.\n\nKartheia compensates for their weaker Flames through aggression. They field larger armies, train citizen-soldiers rather than relying on mercenaries, and expand constantly to create buffer zones. They have pushed into the Marchlands, establishing outposts in contested territory. This generates constant border conflict and has made them the primary target of beastfolk resentment.\n\nThey resent their former mother-city of Lucia and actively compete for trade routes and influence. The rivalry occasionally flares into open conflict, though shared human identity usually prevents full-scale war. Kartheia sees Lucia as decadent and compromised by beastfolk trade; Lucia sees Kartheia as dangerously reckless children who will provoke a war everyone loses.\n\n**Population: 5-7 million** across multiple city-states.",
