    {
      "id": "9ca936f0-e9fd-4d5a-baf2-d267d85a37d4",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Archepyros**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**Archepyros**\n\nArchepyros is the Sacred Isle — a small archipelago that claims to be where the first Flame was kindled during the darkest hour of the Beasttide.\n\nThe story they tell: when the last ships fled burning colonies and the sea itself seemed to reject humanity, 347 refugees landed on a rocky island with nothing. A priestess named Pyrantheia gathered them around a driftwood fire and taught them to *give* — to pour their SOULs into the flame until it became something else entirely. The first Flame kindled on Archepyros. The beastfolk never came.\n\nWhether this is true is disputed. Antheion claims their Flame is older. But everyone *treats* Archepyros as the spiritual origin, and that is what matters.\n\nThe Pyrarch rules — a title meaning \"fire-first,\" the high priest of the original Flame. The holy city of Prytaneia is built around the First Hearth, where the flame has burned for a thousand years without interruption. Pilgrims come from every Thalassic city to touch the stones and add their small SOUL-contribution to the eternal fire.\n\nArchepyros has no army, no navy, only a ceremonial guard. Their defense is their indispensability: they consecrate new Flames (a colony is not legitimate until Archepyros blesses it), mediate disputes between cities, legitimize rulers in contested successions, and pronounce on matters of Civic Flame doctrine. They cannot take sides. Doing so would shatter their authority.\n\n**Population: 1-2 million.** Island-constrained. Prytaneia holds roughly 150,000-200,000, swelling during pilgrimage seasons.",
