      "name": "**The Syndikaia**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**The Syndikaia**\n\nThe Syndikaia (\"the binding\") is not a nation but an alliance — five small cities on a stretch of coast between Lucia and Antheion, none strong enough alone, all bound by mutual defense.\n\nAfter the Beasttide, this coastline was a mess of barely-surviving settlements. The Syndikaia was their solution: five Flames, one pact. An attack on any is an attack on all. Betray the binding, and the other four destroy you before any external enemy can.\n\nThe five cities are Pelorias (largest, most arrogant), Kalethon (oldest Flame of the five), Drymnos (most militaristic), Orthysia (wealthiest from trade), and Kymopolis (smallest, most vulnerable). The Synhedrion council sends representatives from each; major decisions require unanimity, which means everything takes forever.\n\nInternal politics are constant. Pelorias and Kalethon argue over precedence. Drymnos resents its soldiers dying for richer cities. Orthysia threatens to withhold funds whenever outvoted. Kymopolis plays the others against each other.\n\nBut when external threats appear, they unify *fast*. They have survived a thousand years because they understand the alternative. Collectively, their five Flames firing together would devastate any attacker — Lucia and Antheion both want them as clients, but neither wants to test that firepower.\n\n**Population: 4-6 million** across the five cities.",
