    {
      "id": "b226690c-7469-406a-95bc-d4f807657211",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The Brythonic Sphere**",
      "type": "location",
      "description": "**The Brythonic Sphere**\n\nThe northern and western regions of Tieravel face cold outer oceans, misty highlands, dense forests, and boglands. This is the beastfolk heartland — the regions reclaimed during the Beasttide, where the Old Law holds absolute sway once more. The land is considered sacred in ways the mercantile south does not understand.\n\nDuring Imperial occupation, the beastfolk were pushed here — to the margins, the places too cold, too wet, too difficult to garrison profitably. They waited. They remembered. When the Rending came and magic kindled in their SOULs, they swept back across the continent in a tide of liberation and vengeance.\n\nNow the inner coast belongs to humans again, held by their Flames. But the beastfolk hold everything else — and they are patient.",
