    {
      "id": "6561d9bf-3994-45c3-b74b-8dd8312d3323",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Antecentrix**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**Antecentrix**\n\nAntecentrix is a sprawling nation of city-states united under a single banner, the military shield of the beastfolk. Originally a single fortress-city guarding a crucial pass, it expanded through conquest and confederation until it became the hegemon of the outer reaches.\n\nThe nation's founding came during the Beasttide, when scattered beastfolk warriors needed coordination to break Imperial defenses. The first war-chief united the clans through sheer tactical brilliance. The structure remained after liberation — someone had to guard against human resurgence, and Antecentrix had proven they could.\n\nA war-chief commands the unified army, but individual city-states retain local autonomy. The current war-chief is Lupine, though the position has passed between species throughout history. The structure resembles a military confederation more than a unified kingdom.\n\nThe Legions of Antecentrix borrow organizational ideas from Imperial models — learned through a thousand years of fighting them — but adapt them to beastfolk strengths. Lupine heavy infantry forms the core, supported by Feline skirmishers, Elaphine logistics and siege engineering, and Satyr battle-mages.\n\nAntecentrix has pushed practical engineering further than other beastfolk states: siege weapons, fortifications, road-building, standardized equipment. This is somewhat heretical to druid purists who prefer working with the land rather than reshaping it, but the results speak for themselves. They argue that defeating humans requires understanding human methods.\n\nThe rivalry with Hintida defines beastfolk politics. Antecentrix represents martial pragmatism; Hintida represents mystical tradition. They need each other but deeply mistrust each other's methods. Antecentrix sees Hintida as dangerously passive, waiting for ancestors to solve problems that require steel. Hintida sees Antecentrix as spiritually compromised, becoming the enemy to fight the enemy.\n\n**Population: 8-10 million.** The largest fortress-city holds roughly 150,000-200,000.",
