    {
      "id": "1b952d11-c656-4315-823b-5efb7a394428",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Ceunant**",
      "type": "faction",
      "description": "**Ceunant**\n\nThe deep forests of the northwest are so saturated with ancestral memory that outsiders experience waking dreams. This is the domain of Ceunant — a loose confederation of Lupine and Feline clans who never unified into a formal nation.\n\nThere are no kings here, no capitals. Each clan is sovereign within its territory, and they unite only against existential threats. Leadership is earned through demonstrated wisdom and martial prowess, not inherited.\n\nThe Dream-Walkers are druids who specialize in navigating the accumulated SOUL-memories of the forest. They can access knowledge from the dead, commune with ancestors who died millennia ago, even glimpse the world before the Rending — before the Empire came. The risk is losing themselves, spending too long in the dream and forgetting which memories are their own.\n\nOther beastfolk consider Ceunant primitive; humans consider them terrifying. The mist-forests have swallowed armies. Invaders find their supplies rotting, their scouts vanishing, their soldiers waking screaming from nightmares that feel more real than waking life. The ancestors do not welcome strangers.\n\nDuring the Beasttide, the clans of Ceunant emerged from their forests like a nightmare made manifest. They remember things the Empire did — atrocities buried in the archives, massacres the humans have forgotten. They have not forgiven. They never will.\n\n**Population: 2-3 million.** Sparse, scattered, no true cities.",
