    {
      "id": "4d5e76af-1a43-493c-9a0c-1464e46c5745",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Relations in the Tieravel Sphere**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Relations in the Tieravel Sphere**\n\nThe beastfolk nations maintain complex relationships shaped by their shared heritage and divergent responses to the human presence.\n\nHintida sees itself as the spiritual authority over all beastfolk, a claim that Noctria tolerates, Antecentrix resents, and Ysgolion politely ignores. Pilgrims and tribute flow to the High Magi, but political obedience does not follow.\n\nNoctria maintains trade relationships with everyone, including the human city-states. This pragmatism makes them wealthy and influential but also suspect. Hintida druids question whether New Gloria has sold its soul; Antecentrix generals question whether Noctrian gold would flow if war came. The Saltraeth maintain complicated relations — trading partners in peace, occasional raiders of each other's shipping.\n\nAntecentrix positions itself as the shield of the beastfolk, the military power that keeps human expansion in check. They demand recognition and resources from other beastfolk nations, arguing that someone must bear the cost of defense. Ysgolion feeds their armies; this is acknowledged less often than the Legions' martial glory.\n\nYsgolion supplies everyone and is thanked by no one. Their quiet resentment grows.\n\nThe Saltraeth remain apart from land-based politics, acknowledging no authority but their own clan-structures. They raid human shipping but also trade with Noctria and hire out to Antecentrix when sea-power is needed. Other beastfolk find them strange — too changed by the sea, too willing to deal with anyone.\n\nCeunant remains apart, neither acknowledging Hintida's spiritual authority nor joining Antecentrix's military confederation. They are called upon in times of crisis and otherwise left alone. Their Dream-Walkers hold memories that make other beastfolk uncomfortable — proof of what the Empire did, and what was done in return during the Beasttide.\n\nAmong the human powers, Antheion dominates through age and agricultural wealth. Lucia dominates through naval supremacy and financial networks. Skaros commands respect through military reputation. Kartheia expands aggressively. The Syndikaia tries to remain neutral. Archepyros mediates and consecrates. They cooperate against beastfolk threats but compete fiercely otherwise.\n\nThe Marchlands suffer whoever wins.",
