    {
      "id": "0fd494de-52f7-4700-9898-15d200e90810",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The Raft-Cities**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**The Raft-Cities**\n\nFloating communities that follow fishing and trade routes rather than claiming land. The most heterodox population in Yolcentla—their religion has drifted so far from orthodoxy that other humans barely recognize it.\n\n**No Fixed Shrines**\n\nRaft-City religion is entirely portable. No temples, no sacred sites tied to land. The sun is still acknowledged, but the sea has become nearly equal—and the Raft-Cities have developed practices around the *deep*, the dark waters below, that other humans find disturbing.\n\nThey believe the Primordial isn't just below the earth—it's below the water. The deep ocean *is* the accumulated dead, vast and patient. When a Raft-City native dies, they're given to the sea—a burial that other Yolcentla cultures consider horrifying. *How will their tonal rise if they're dragged down?*\n\nThe Raft-Cities answer: maybe tonal doesn't need to rise. Maybe the deep is another kind of destination. They're vague about details, which only makes other humans more suspicious.\n\n**Community as Shrine**\n\nWhat the Raft-Cities do venerate intensely is *each other*. A raft-community is family, crew, congregation, and nation all in one. The bonds between raft-mates are the closest thing they have to sacred architecture.\n\nNew members are adopted through serious ritual. Leaving is possible but painful—a kind of exile. Betraying raft-mates is the worst crime: not just social rupture but spiritual catastrophe.\n\n**Raft-City Oaths and Exclamations**\n\n- *\"Deep and sun!\"* — Basic exclamation; both cosmic powers\n- *\"By my raft\"* — Oath invoking community; the most serious Raft-City promise\n- *\"Sinking\"* — Curse; something failing badly\n- *\"Float on\"* — Encouragement; keep going, stay above water\n- *\"The deep waits\"* — Acknowledgment of mortality; not fearful, just factual\n- *\"Land-bound\"* — Insult; someone stuck, limited, unable to move with the world\n- *\"What raft?\"* — Challenge; \"who are your people?\" (a stranger with no community is suspect)\n\n**Raft-City Gestures**\n\nWhen making oaths, Raft-City people place both hands flat on the deck (or whatever surface is available)—connecting to the raft, to the community, to what's real.\n\nWhen greeting raft-mates after separation, the embrace is full—arms around each other, heads together. These people are everything to each other.\n\nWhen speaking of the dead given to the sea, the gesture is palms down, pressing toward the water (or floor). Not the upward gesture for rising tonal—a downward acknowledgment that the dead went *below*, and that's okay.",
