      "name": "**Water Acknowledgments**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Water Acknowledgments**\n\nThe river is sacred, and water generally carries that sanctity. Zhiran people have small habits around water that outsiders find peculiar.\n\nWhen crossing a bridge, a brief pause at the midpoint—just a heartbeat of stillness. Not prayer exactly, but acknowledgment. *You're above the current. Show respect.*\n\nWhen drinking water (not tea, not alcohol—plain water), a small nod before the first sip. Some people touch the cup to their forehead briefly. Water is the Great Confluence in miniature; you're drinking what your ancestors became.\n\nWhen it rains, especially the first rain after drought: people will stop and turn their faces up, mouths slightly open. Accepting heaven's blessing. Children are encouraged to do this; it's considered good for their cultivation.",
