    {
      "id": "a70b805a-1083-4f7e-93d0-5445aa3bb34e",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Zhiran Oaths and Exclamations**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Zhiran Oaths and Exclamations**\n\n*Frustration/anger:*\n- *\"Nì!\"* — The opposite of shùn; fighting the current. Used like \"damn!\"\n- *\"Against the current!\"* — Something's going wrong, nothing's working\n- *\"Muddy waters\"* — Situation is confused, unclear, probably someone's fault\n\n*Surprise:*\n- *\"Tiān!\"* — \"Heaven!\" The basic sacred exclamation\n- *\"Ancestors!\"* — Can be surprise or exasperation\n- *\"What current is this?\"* — \"What the hell is going on?\"\n\n*Emphasis/swearing truth:*\n- *\"Heaven witnesses\"* — Formal, serious\n- *\"By the river\"* — More casual but still binding\n- *\"May I flow against\"* — \"May I struggle forever if I'm lying\"\n- *\"On my ancestors' waters\"* — Invoking the dead; very serious\n\n*Relief:*\n- *\"The current holds\"* — Crisis passed, natural order maintained\n- *\"Shùn\"* — Just the word, exhaled; \"okay, that's settled\"\n- *\"Clear water\"* — Situation resolved, clarity achieved\n\n*Resignation/acceptance:*\n- *\"Shùn, then\"* — Accepting something you can't change; \"it is what it is\"\n- *\"The river goes where it goes\"* — Fatalistic but not bitter",
