      "name": "**Göran Oaths and Exclamations**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Göran Oaths and Exclamations**\n\n*Frustration/anger:*\n- *\"Windless!\"* — The worst state; cursing something as stagnant\n- *\"Khuur rot it\"* — Contradictory (wind doesn't rot) but expressive\n- *\"Settled blood\"* — Insulting something as domesticated, tamed, dead-while-living\n\n*Surprise:*\n- *\"Khuur!\"* — The basic exclamation\n- *\"Wind's teeth!\"* — Stronger, for genuine shock\n- *\"What storm is this?\"* — \"What's happening?\"\n\n*Emphasis/swearing truth:*\n- *\"By the eternal wind\"* — Standard serious oath\n- *\"May khuur abandon me\"* — Strongest oath; if I lie, let me be windless\n- *\"My ancestors hear\"* — They're riding the khuur; they're always listening\n\n*Relief:*\n- *\"The wind holds\"* — Crisis passed\n- *\"Still riding\"* — We're okay, still in motion\n- *\"Khuur laughs\"* — Fortune smiled; things worked out (wind is playful)\n\n*Greeting/parting:*\n- *\"Khuur with you\"* — Standard greeting and farewell both\n- *\"Ride far\"* — Farewell with good wishes\n- *\"Strong wind at your back\"* — Blessing for a journey",
