      "name": "**Vertical Awareness**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Vertical Awareness**\n\nFelines of Drakhar are constantly aware of height. Their observances reflect this.\n\nMorning begins with *climbing something*—even if just a rock, a roof, a tree. You greet the day from height, facing the peaks where the ancestors watch. Looking *down* at sunrise is mildly taboo; you should be looking up or across, toward the mountains that hold your dead.\n\nIn homes built into mountainsides (as most are), the household shrine is always in the highest room or the highest corner. Ancestors want to be high. Placing ancestor tablets in a low position is deeply disrespectful.",
