      "name": "**The Height Greeting**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**The Height Greeting**\n\nWhen two Felines meet, there's a subtle negotiation of vertical position. The one who positions themselves slightly lower is showing respect. But this isn't like Zhiran bowing—it's more fluid, more like cats finding their places. A younger Feline might crouch slightly, or stay on a lower rock. An elder might accept this or gesture them up to equal height as a kindness.\n\nWhen speaking of something important, Felines tend to *climb* during the conversation—pacing upward, finding higher ground. Ideas are easier to discuss from height.",
