      "name": "**Drakhar Oaths and Exclamations**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Drakhar Oaths and Exclamations**\n\n*Frustration/anger:*\n- *\"Flatlander!\"* — Insult for anything/anyone low, grounded, spiritually diminished\n- *\"Valley-cursed\"* — Something that keeps going wrong\n- *\"Fallen stone\"* — A failure, a descent, something that lost its height\n\n*Surprise:*\n- *\"Lungta!\"* — The basic exclamation\n- *\"Peaks!\"* — Shorter, sharper\n- *\"What height?\"* — \"What is this?\" (implying: where does this rank in importance?)\n\n*Emphasis/swearing truth:*\n- *\"By the high places\"* — Standard oath\n- *\"May I fall\"* — Serious oath; if I lie, let me lose my height\n- *\"My dead witness\"* — Invoking ancestors in the peaks\n- *\"On the stone\"* — On the lungta itself; very serious\n\n*Fear:*\n- *\"Lost to lungta\"* — The fate of those who die abroad; genuine horror\n- *\"Wandering low\"* — A soul that can't find the heights; pitiable and terrifying\n\n*Relief:*\n- *\"Lungta holds\"* — Crisis passed, still connected to the heights\n- *\"Still climbing\"* — We're okay\n- *\"The peak sees\"* — Equivalent to \"God willing\" but in reverse—the peaks approve",
