      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Drakhar Gestures**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Drakhar Gestures**\n\nWhen speaking of the dead, Felines look *up*. Not a dramatic head-tilt, just a brief upward glance. The dead are above. Always.\n\nWhen making a serious promise, a Feline places their hand flat on stone—any stone, but preferably bedrock or mountain stone. *Promising on the lungta, on the mountain itself.*\n\nWhen greeting someone returning from a journey, especially from low lands, there's a ritual of *touching their shoulders and looking them over*—checking that they came back whole, that they didn't leave pieces of themselves below. A safe return from the lowlands is not assumed.",
