      "name": "**Earth Contact**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Earth Contact**\n\nThe beastfolk of the Old Law maintain physical contact with the land in ways that seem excessive to outsiders.\n\nMorning begins with bare feet on soil—even in cold weather, even briefly. You *ground yourself* before the day starts, reminding your gwraidd where it connects. Homes have floors of packed earth or wood, but there's usually a spot where the bare ground is accessible for this purpose.\n\nWhen entering a new area—a different clan's territory, a sacred grove, a place you haven't been before—you touch the ground with your palm before proceeding. *Asking permission. Introducing yourself to the local dead.* Omitting this is rude to both the living and the ancestors.",
