      "name": "**Mealtime**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Mealtime**\n\nBefore eating, a small portion goes directly to the earth—pushed into soil, dropped through floorboards, scattered on ground. The words are simple: *\"For those below\"* or just *\"Gwraidd.\"* This feeds the ancestors in the most literal way.\n\nWater is poured, not thrown. *The earth drinks, doesn't catch.*\n\nIn homes, there's often a small pit or opening in the floor near the hearth specifically for these offerings. It's never cleaned out; the earth takes what it takes.",
