      "name": "**Tieravel Beastfolk Oaths and Exclamations**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Tieravel Beastfolk Oaths and Exclamations**\n\n*Frustration/anger:*\n- *\"Rootless!\"* — The worst insult; no gwraidd, no ancestors, no belonging\n- *\"Shallow-planted\"* — Mildly insulting; weak gwraidd, weak connection\n- *\"Surface-walker\"* — Someone who doesn't understand depth; often applied to humans\n- *\"Blighted ground\"* — A situation that's gone bad\n\n*Surprise:*\n- *\"Gwraidd!\"* — Basic exclamation\n- *\"Deep roots!\"* — Stronger surprise\n- *\"What grows here?\"* — \"What is happening?\"\n\n*Emphasis/swearing truth:*\n- *\"By my roots\"* — Standard oath\n- *\"On the bones below\"* — Swearing on buried ancestors; very serious\n- *\"May my gwraidd wither\"* — Strongest oath; if I lie, let me be severed from my dead\n- *\"The land hears\"* — The earth itself witnesses; formal and binding\n\n*Sorrow/loss:*\n- *\"The roots ache\"* — Something sad is happening\n- *\"Torn from the ground\"* — Exile, loss, severance from home\n- *\"The dead are troubled\"* — Something is very wrong\n\n*Relief:*\n- *\"The ground holds\"* — Crisis passed\n- *\"Deep roots\"* — Can be relief or reassurance: we're stable, we'll survive\n- *\"The ancestors are quiet\"* — No spiritual disturbance; things are okay",
