      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Tieravel Beastfolk Gestures**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Tieravel Beastfolk Gestures**\n\nThe *ground-touch*—palm to earth—happens constantly. When swearing, when grateful, when passing a burial site, when speaking of the dead. It's as automatic as breathing.\n\nWhen passing standing stones (the Singing Stones marking power points), beastfolk pause and place both palms on the stone if possible. Not prayer—*greeting*. The stones are where gwraidd is strongest; you acknowledge that.\n\nWhen speaking of someone who died on this land, the gesture is palm-down, pressing toward the ground. *They're below. They're part of this.* When speaking of someone who died abroad (tragedy), the gesture is palm-up, fingers spread—*reaching for something that isn't there.*",
