      "name": "**The Citizenship Rituals**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**The Citizenship Rituals**\n\nFull citizens participate in small collective rituals that non-citizens cannot. Most visible: the *weekly flame-gathering* where citizens assemble in neighborhood groups to \"feed\" local shrine flames with a moment of collective focus. This takes only minutes, but it's obligatory and tracked. Missing too many marks you as weak in koinon.\n\nNon-citizens (foreigners, slaves, resident beastfolk) are not allowed to participate and often visibly step back during these moments. This small exclusion, repeated weekly, reinforces the two-tiered society more than any law.",
