      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Thalassic Oaths and Exclamations**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Thalassic Oaths and Exclamations**\n\n*Frustration/anger:*\n- *\"Ash!\"* — What's left when fire dies; something worthless\n- *\"Cold!\"* — A situation without koinon; something wrong\n- *\"Flame-dark\"* — The worst state; fire gone out entirely\n- *\"Exile's portion\"* — Bitterly noting that something is worthless/disconnected\n\n*Surprise:*\n- *\"Koinon!\"* — Basic exclamation\n- *\"Flame!\"* — Shorter, sharper\n- *\"Sacred fire!\"* — Strong surprise\n- *\"What burns?\"* — \"What's happening?\"\n\n*Emphasis/swearing truth:*\n- *\"By the Hearth\"* — Standard oath, referring to city's central Flame\n- *\"On the koinon\"* — Swearing on the collective; serious\n- *\"May my spark go out\"* — Strongest citizen's oath; let me be severed from the city if I lie\n- *\"The Flame sees\"* — Formal witnessing invocation\n\n*Civic pride/solidarity:*\n- *\"Koinon, friend\"* — Greeting between citizens; acknowledging shared fire\n- *\"We burn together\"* — Solidarity phrase; we're in this together\n- *\"The Flame rises\"* — Our city is strong; things are going well\n\n*Contempt (for outsiders):*\n- *\"Cold-blood\"* — Non-citizen; someone outside the koinon\n- *\"No hearth\"* — Homeless in the spiritual sense; rootless\n- *\"Ashed out\"* — Someone who's been exiled; lost their citizenship",
