      "name": "**Thalassic Gestures**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Thalassic Gestures**\n\nThe *flame-touch*—fingers to lips, then extended toward fire—happens whenever passing significant flames. The gesture at home flames is simpler: just touching the lamp or its holder.\n\nWhen greeting fellow citizens, a palm-out gesture toward each other, fingers spread, like warming hands at a shared fire. This isn't done with non-citizens.\n\nWhen speaking of the city itself—its glory, its history, its survival—citizens often place a hand over their heart. *Your spark is part of the greater fire.*\n\nWhen speaking of exile, of those cast out, the gesture is closing the hand into a fist and pulling it back toward the chest—*drawing in, closing out.* Citizens don't like to think about exile; the gesture is almost involuntary, protective.",
