      "name": "**The Three Fires**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**The Three Fires**\n\nThe founding Compact is symbolized by three flames—one for humans, one for the Elaphine valley communities, one for the Feline mountain clans. The Three Fires temple in Samhwa maintains these literal flames, and the symbol (three flames, or three vertical lines) appears everywhere: on coins, above doorways, worked into fabric patterns.\n\nThis is the touchstone of Goryun identity more than abstract forge philosophy. The Three Fires represent *what we built together, what we chose.*",
