    {
      "id": "7a8e5daa-d75d-40fc-8986-0397e251bf40",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Meals**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Meals**\n\nBefore eating, a brief pause—hand flat on the table or held over the food. The words vary by household: *\"For those who prepared this,\"* or *\"Strength to the work ahead,\"* or simply a moment of stillness. Some families invoke ancestors; others don't. Goryun is less ancestor-focused than Zhiran; the dead are respected but not constantly consulted.\n\nThe emphasis is on *presence*—being fully here for the meal, not rushing through it. Eating while walking or working is considered low-class, a habit of people who haven't mastered themselves.",
