    {
      "id": "6946aaf7-fdd4-470b-872d-8daa78ae61c2",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Goryun Oaths and Exclamations**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Goryun Oaths and Exclamations**\n\n*Frustration/anger:*\n- *\"Three Fires!\"* — Basic strong exclamation, like \"God damn it\"\n- *\"Ash and smoke\"* — Something's gone wrong, burned up\n- *\"Cold hell\"* — When something is frustratingly stuck, passionless, unmovable\n- *\"Cracked\"* — Someone or something that failed under pressure\n\n*Surprise:*\n- *\"Fires!\"* — Short form of Three Fires; basic surprise\n- *\"What wind?\"* — \"What's happening?\" (less fire-focused; wind stirs fire up)\n- *\"Heaven and earth\"* — Stronger surprise; borrowed from Zhiran but naturalized\n\n*Emphasis/swearing truth:*\n- *\"By the Three Fires\"* — Standard oath; the most common serious invocation\n- *\"On the Compact\"* — Serious; invoking the founding agreement\n- *\"May my fire die\"* — Strong personal oath; let my passion extinguish if I lie\n- *\"My ancestors hear\"* — Formal, used in legal or ceremonial contexts\n\n*Encouragement:*\n- *\"Hold steady\"* — Keep going; maintain your center\n- *\"You have fire\"* — Praising someone's passion or courage\n- *\"The heat passes\"* — This difficulty is temporary; you'll come through it\n\n*Assessment:*\n- *\"Good center\"* — Praising someone's balance, their dallyeom (without using the formal term)\n- *\"Steady hands\"* — Someone reliable under pressure\n- *\"Too hot\"* — Someone letting passion overcome discipline\n- *\"Too cold\"* — Someone suppressing too much; passionless, lifeless\n\n*Resolution/success:*\n- *\"Well held\"* — Praise for getting through something difficult with grace\n- *\"The fire's still there\"* — We survived; we're still ourselves\n- *\"Dallyeom!\"* — As a toast or before battle; formal, deliberately invoking the philosophy",
      "hiddenInfo": null,
      "aliases": [
        "**Goryun Oaths and Exclamations**"
