    {
      "id": "5889b5f3-60e1-482a-810f-f7a6218922a1",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What's Different from Zhiran**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What's Different from Zhiran**\n\nGoryun people often compare themselves to Zhiran, sometimes favorably, sometimes not.\n\nWhere Zhiran says \"find shùn\" (align with the current), Goryun says \"hold steady\" (maintain your center against the current). The Zhiran ideal is to stop struggling; the Goryun ideal is to struggle *well*.\n\nWhere Zhiran values stillness before action, Goryun values movement before stillness. Tea after exertion, not meditation before it.\n\nWhere Zhiran talks about the river taking you where you need to go, Goryun talks about walking your own path. Human agency matters here. You are not driftwood.\n\nGoryun people find Zhiran philosophy somewhat fatalistic, even defeatist. Zhiran people find Goryun philosophy exhausting, even arrogant. Both are caricatures, but the tension is real.",
