    {
      "id": "23604a9c-4117-4d09-b8c9-79c01a06c454",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Light Attention**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Light Attention**\n\nPavonines are very aware of light and how it falls on them. Positioning yourself in good light isn't vain—it's helping your kagami shine.\n\nMorning prayers (such as they are) face the sunrise. The words vary, but the theme is consistent: *\"Heaven sees me. I show myself truly.\"* Then a display—brief, personal, genuine.\n\nImportant conversations happen in well-lit spaces when possible. Speaking of serious matters in darkness feels wrong to Pavonines—how can you show your kagami if no one can see you?",
