      "name": "**Aohane Oaths and Exclamations**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Aohane Oaths and Exclamations**\n\n*Frustration/anger:*\n- *\"Molted!\"* — Something's gone wrong; a mess\n- *\"Dull-feather\"* — Insult; someone whose kagami doesn't shine\n- *\"Hidden!\"* — Accusation that someone's concealing themselves; serious criticism\n- *\"False colors\"* — Someone displaying what they're not; deeply offensive\n\n*Surprise:*\n- *\"Kagami!\"* — Basic exclamation\n- *\"Heaven's light!\"* — Stronger\n- *\"What displays?\"* — \"What's happening?\"\n\n*Emphasis/swearing truth:*\n- *\"By my plumage\"* — Standard oath; swearing on your display\n- *\"Heaven sees\"* — Invoking divine witness\n- *\"May my feathers dull\"* — Strongest oath; let my kagami fade if I lie\n- *\"True colors\"* — \"I'm being honest\"\n\n*Admiration:*\n- *\"Bright kagami!\"* — Greeting, or praise for someone being authentically themselves\n- *\"Full display\"* — High praise; someone showing their complete true self\n- *\"Heaven approves\"* — Something is as it should be\n\n*Contempt:*\n- *\"Ground-crawler\"* — Insult for anyone low, hidden, non-displaying\n- *\"Shadow-skulker\"* — Someone who hides their true self\n- *\"Broken molt\"* — Someone whose renewal went wrong; pitiable or contemptible",
