    {
      "id": "7a88109a-1e17-411b-ab0f-6d8ff86439c8",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The Aegis — Luna**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**The Aegis — Luna**\n\nThe Aegis don't have religion in the Terran sense—they have PRIMA, who is more terrifying than any god because she's *real* and she *notices things*. Their culture revolves around a central contradiction: they have emotions but aren't supposed to. Their language evolved to express feelings through technical terminology, creating constant subtext. Everyone knows what's really being said; no one acknowledges it directly.",
