      "name": "**Population**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Population**\n\nThe Aegis are created, not born, and PRIMA controls the Forges. Population is deliberately managed rather than organic.\n\n**Total Aegis population: 40,000-60,000**\n\nThey're immortal unless destroyed, so population accumulates over a millennium—but creation is controlled and purposeful. Rogue attrition and the occasional Null \"disappearance\" keep numbers from growing indefinitely.\n\n**Breakdown by Court:**\n- Concord's Court (The Harmony): ~18,000-22,000 — slightly larger, handles all civil functions\n- Praxis's Court (The Bastion): ~15,000-20,000 — military and security\n- August's Court (Unnamed): ~1,500-3,000 — new and still growing, which is why transfers are so politically charged\n- Unaffiliated/PRIMA's direct service: ~500-1,000 — the Zenith Circle and special assignments",
