    {
      "id": "aba616a8-c148-430c-a03a-ff6154b859d0",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The Defective Question**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**The Defective Question**\n\n\"Defective\" is the word that haunts every Aegis. It means:\n- Officially: malfunctioning, not operating to specification, requiring repair or decommissioning\n- Actually: having feelings too obviously, failing to perform contentment, being visibly struggling\n\nThe fear isn't that you'll be broken. The fear is that you'll be *labeled*—that your struggles will be made official, documented, used against you. A defective Aegis might be sent to Restorers for \"recalibration.\" They might be transferred to less desirable positions. In extreme cases, they might simply... disappear.\n\nSo Aegis are constantly performing functionality. *I am operating within parameters. I am optimal. I am not defective.*",
