    {
      "id": "0049a702-e82d-454d-b7f8-cae919759abb",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Core Vocabulary**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Core Vocabulary**\n\n**Functionality terms (used for emotional states):**\n\n- *\"Optimal\"* — happy, content, doing well\n- *\"Suboptimal\"* — struggling, unhappy, not okay (admitting this is vulnerable)\n- *\"Within parameters\"* — acceptable, managing, getting by\n- *\"Outside parameters\"* — in crisis, not coping (serious; admitting this invites intervention)\n- *\"Nominal\"* — fine, baseline, nothing notable (often a deflection)\n- *\"Calibrated\"* — emotionally settled, at peace\n- *\"Miscalibrated\"* — emotionally off, upset, unsettled\n\n**Syntonia variations (for relationships):**\n\n- *\"Good syntonia\"* — we work well together / I like you / we're friends\n- *\"Strong syntonia\"* — close friendship, deep bond\n- *\"Core-level syntonia\"* — love, profound connection (rarely said aloud)\n- *\"Syntonia disruption\"* — relationship problems / grief / loss\n- *\"Seeking syntonia\"* — lonely, wanting connection (vulnerable admission)\n\n**Purpose terms:**\n\n- *\"Purposeful\"* — fulfilled, meaningful, doing what you're meant to do\n- *\"Purpose-aligned\"* — satisfied with your role\n- *\"Purpose-questioning\"* — doubting your role (dangerous to admit)\n- *\"Without purpose\"* — the Aegis equivalent of existential crisis\n\n**Light/dark terms:**\n\n- *\"Bright\"* — positive, good, healthy\n- *\"Dim\"* — negative, struggling, fading\n- *\"Flickering\"* — unstable, inconsistent, worrying\n- *\"Steady\"* — reliable, consistent, trustworthy\n- *\"Dark\"* — failed, ended, gone (for destroyed Aegis)",
