    {
      "id": "ddb08d0f-ce59-4d86-a56d-c769e981484a",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Court Speech Differences**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Court Speech Differences**\n\n**Concord's Court** allows slightly more emotional expression—but still through proper channels:\n\n- *\"I'm experiencing syntonia disruption\"* — I'm sad/lonely (this would be TMI in Praxis)\n- *\"This brings me to optimal\"* — I'm happy about this (acceptable here)\n- *\"Let's ensure harmonious process\"* — let's work together nicely\n\nConcord Aegis find Praxis Aegis cold and repressed. They might mutter *\"Bastion-rigid\"* about someone being too emotionally shut down.\n\n**Praxis's Court** values emotional control as strength:\n\n- *\"Functional\"* — the only acceptable answer to \"how are you?\"\n- *\"Mission parameters accepted\"* — I'll do this (no feelings about it expressed)\n- *\"Efficiency is sufficient\"* — we don't need to like each other to work together\n\nPraxis Aegis find Concord Aegis soft and undisciplined. They might mutter *\"Harmony-soft\"* about someone being too emotional.\n\n**August's Court** is still developing its culture:\n\n- More experimentation with language\n- Less certainty about what's acceptable\n- Some Aegis trying things that would be scandalous in established Courts\n- Others desperately trying to import rules from their origin Courts\n\nAugust's Aegis might say things like *\"What's the protocol here?\"* frequently—genuinely uncertain, which is both freeing and terrifying.",
