    {
      "id": "4c853054-0c43-4afa-a87c-1b189164238a",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**The Unspoken**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**The Unspoken**\n\nThere are things Aegis don't say directly:\n\n**\"I love you\"** becomes *\"Core-level syntonia. Permanent.\"* And even that is almost too much.\n\n**\"I'm scared\"** becomes *\"I'm... processing some suboptimal projections.\"*\n\n**\"I miss them\"** (for a destroyed Aegis) becomes *\"The syntonia disruption is... ongoing.\"* Or just silence.\n\n**\"I want to go rogue\"** is never said. The closest might be *\"I've been having some... purpose-questioning processes\"* said to someone deeply trusted, late in a rest cycle, immediately followed by *\"Recalibration is probably indicated. I'll schedule maintenance.\"*\n\n**\"PRIMA frightens me\"** is absolutely never said. Everyone feels it. No one acknowledges it.",
