    {
      "id": "c923b996-575b-4410-a026-875158387e06",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**Aegis Gestures**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**Aegis Gestures**\n\nAegis are beings of light, so their gestures involve light-manipulation:\n\n**Dimming slightly** — deference, submission, making yourself smaller. Done when an Archon passes, or when corrected by a superior.\n\n**Brightening** — attention, engagement, approval. An Aegis brightens when interested or pleased. Trying to suppress this is difficult; it's the equivalent of trying not to smile.\n\n**Flickering** — distress, instability, strong emotion. Aegis try very hard not to flicker in public. Visible flickering is embarrassing at best, evidence of defect at worst.\n\n**Steady glow** — calm, controlled, optimal. The ideal state. Maintaining steady light during stress is a skill.\n\n**Light-reaching** — extending your light toward another Aegis. Intimate. Done during syntonia rituals, or when comforting someone in private. In public, even a small light-reach toward someone is notable.\n\n**Withdrawing light** — pulling your glow inward, closing off. Rejection, anger, or self-protection. Doing this to someone is a clear message: *I don't want connection with you right now.*",
