    {
      "id": "848d0ab1-c0e9-4612-893a-3b039d705077",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What the Aegis Believe About Terrans**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What the Aegis Believe About Terrans**\n\n**\"Humans are primitive.\"** Aegis culture officially views humans as failed prototypes—beings who had the potential for greatness but chose stagnation. The truth is more complicated. Humans invented the Aegis. Human scientists created PRIMA. The technology the Aegis now use descends from human innovation. But admitting this creates uncomfortable questions about who the \"perfect beings\" really are, so Aegis education glosses over the details of their own origin.\n\n**\"Beastfolk are irrelevant animals.\"** Imperial propaganda portrayed beastfolk as subhuman, and the Aegis inherited this view uncritically. Most Aegis have never actually observed beastfolk society—they watch Terra from orbit, seeing cities and armies, but the nuance is lost. They do not understand that beastfolk created magic, that Satyr mages rival anything the old Empire produced, that the \"animals\" built civilizations while the Aegis argued about court politics.\n\n**\"Terran magic is crude instinct.\"** Aegis who study Terran magic are rare and often dismissed. The official position is that SOUL-channeling is a desperate adaptation, inferior to proper technology. In truth, Terran magic has developed sophisticated theory and practice over a millennium—the Aegis simply haven't bothered to learn it.",
