    {
      "id": "217d9dbb-819c-4c23-a54e-66448ec681df",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Terrans Believe About the Aegis**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Terrans Believe About the Aegis**\n\n**\"The sky-demons are gods.\"** Common folk across Terra know almost nothing accurate about the Aegis. In Yolcentla, they are sometimes conflated with celestial beings—either servants of the sun or minions of the moon, depending on local theology. The idea that they are artificial, created by humans, would be considered blasphemous or insane.\n\n**\"They could destroy us anytime.\"** Many who know of the Aegis assume they choose not to descend out of indifference or some cosmic game. The truth—that they *cannot* harm humans and that their technology fails in high-magic environments—would reshape every strategic calculation on Terra. No one knows.\n\n**\"They are unified.\"** Terrans who think about the Aegis at all imagine a single will, a hive-mind perhaps. The fractious politics of the Courts, the rivalries between Archons, the silent dissent and the rogue defectors—none of this is known below.",
