    {
      "id": "f994b6ce-6299-4696-a604-c9fa8c355fd1",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Yolitzac Believes About Everyone Else**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Yolitzac Believes About Everyone Else**\n\n**\"We are the true heirs of the Empire.\"** Yolitzac's entire identity rests on this claim. The reality: every region of Yolcentla has equal claim to Imperial heritage, and the Empire itself was a constructed ideology, not an ancient tradition. Yolitzac's \"pure\" Imperial customs are a thousand years removed from the original, shaped by drift, loss, and invention.\n\n**\"The outer kingdoms are spiritually degraded.\"** Yolitzac scholars view Yolica's \"feeding the age\" theology as dangerous heterodoxy and Oliken's prophecy-focused faith as superstition. They consider Yullqa barely civilized. In truth, all these traditions share common roots, and Yolitzac's rigid dualism is just as much a post-Rending innovation as anything else.\n\n**\"Beastfolk are incapable of civilization.\"** Despite having almost no contact with beastfolk, Yolitzac maintains confident disdain. The few beastfolk traders who reach the continent are treated as curiosities. The idea that beastfolk built cities larger than Tonallan, developed sophisticated philosophy, and maintain complex governance would be dismissed as propaganda.",
      "hiddenInfo": null,
      "aliases": [
