    {
      "id": "abf11dea-f840-4ebf-86f4-1a2951efc2c5",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Others Believe About Yolitzac**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Others Believe About Yolitzac**\n\n**\"They practice human sacrifice constantly.\"** Other Yolcentla regions exaggerate Yolitzac's sacrificial practices. Yes, blood offerings occur—but they are far less common than outsiders imagine, mostly symbolic, and rarely fatal. The lurid tales of hearts cut from living chests are based on rare extreme rituals, not daily practice.\n\n**\"The Centeotl is a living god.\"** Many believe the ruler of Yolitzac has genuine divine power. The truth: the Centeotl is a political figure whose \"divine\" status is useful theater. Their actual magical abilities are no greater than any trained mage.\n\n**\"They never stopped being the Empire.\"** Yolica, Oliken, and Yullqa all view Yolitzac with a mix of resentment and fear, assuming it maintains Imperial-level organization and ambition. In reality, Yolitzac's bureaucracy is calcified, its military is mediocre, and its reach extends little beyond its core territories.",
