      "name": "**What Yolica Kingdoms Get Wrong**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Yolica Kingdoms Get Wrong**\n\n**\"Cuauhtemoc thinks Xochimilca are cowards.\"** The martial kingdom views its agricultural neighbors as soft, when in fact Xochimilca's subtle magic and control of food supplies gives them leverage Cuauhtemoc cannot match.\n\n**\"Micteca's death-priests are necromancers.\"** Other Yolica kingdoms whisper that Micteca practices forbidden arts. The truth: their Primordial communion is no more \"necromancy\" than any other SOUL-magic. They simply specialize in death-adjacent work that others find uncomfortable.",
