      "name": "**What Yullqa Gets Wrong About Others**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Yullqa Gets Wrong About Others**\n\n**\"Lowlanders don't understand reciprocity.\"** Yullqa views coastal and valley peoples as spiritually impoverished, missing the ayni principle. They fail to recognize that every culture has exchange ethics—just framed differently.\n\n**\"The Empire was purely evil.\"** Yullqa's oral traditions paint the United Empire as a demonic force. While the Empire was brutal, it was also complex—many Yullqa communities actually had relatively stable relationships with Imperial administrators. This nuance has been erased from memory.",
