    {
      "id": "9f970937-de5a-43fc-b26d-5370350a3ef8",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Zhiran Believes About Itself**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Zhiran Believes About Itself**\n\n**\"The Five Natures creates genuine equality.\"** Orthodox Heliushuo teaches that all species have complementary strengths, implying balance. In practice, Satyrs dominate magical and political positions, Elaphines fill bureaucratic roles, and Lupines and Felines are pushed toward military and manual labor. Humans are the \"Passion problem.\" The system is a hierarchy wearing the mask of harmony.\n\n**\"Integration is voluntary.\"** Zhiran tells itself that beastfolk and humans chose civilization. The reality is messier—some chose, some were conquered, some had no alternatives. The Lupines of Beifang are descended from those who fled Göran or were exiled; calling their presence \"voluntary\" ignores the circumstances.\n\n**\"The examination system is meritocratic.\"** Wealthy families buy tutors, examination passes, and appointments. Rural candidates compete against those with every advantage. The system rewards merit *among those who can access it*, which is a very different thing.",
