    {
      "id": "38750b46-36da-42ed-9fe0-1a2f4f3a06d3",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Zhiran Believes About the Barbarians**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Zhiran Believes About the Barbarians**\n\n**\"Göran Lupines are mindless raiders.\"** Zhiran sees the steppe peoples as an undifferentiated threat, motivated by pure aggression. The complex clan politics, the spiritual significance of khuur, the sophisticated mounted warfare tactics—none of this penetrates Zhiran's stereotypes. A Lupine is a Lupine is a threat.\n\n**\"Drakhar Felines are savages in caves.\"** The image of Felines as primitive ambush predators ignores their intricate pride politics, their sacred relationship with lungta, and their engineering achievements in mountain terrain. Zhiran has been fighting Drakhar for centuries without understanding why the mountains have never fallen.\n\n**\"They would be happier if they integrated.\"** The sincere Zhiran belief that barbarians suffer from their barbarism, that they secretly envy civilization. The Göran and Drakhar peoples find this attitude baffling and insulting. They rejected integration deliberately.",
