    {
      "id": "8a832933-c5a0-4fb9-9a4d-ced2b8b82d8f",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Zhiran Believes About Goryun**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Zhiran Believes About Goryun**\n\n**\"They are almost civilized, but...\"** Zhiran views Goryun as Zhiran-adjacent, having adopted examination culture and some Heliushuo concepts. The condescension is constant: Goryun is seen as the student who never quite graduated, the peripheral kingdom that aspires to be a real civilization.\n\n**\"Jeongyeol is just misunderstood Heliushuo.\"** Zhiran scholars assume Goryun philosophy must be derivative. The idea that Jeongyeol represents a genuine alternative—that humans might achieve harmony without beastfolk—is uncomfortable enough to dismiss.\n\n**\"Their human-majority population is dangerous.\"** Zhiran quietly worries about Goryun as proof that humans can build sophisticated civilization independently. This undermines the entire Five Natures framework.",
