      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Zhiran Believes About Aohane**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Zhiran Believes About Aohane**\n\n**\"They are civilized but strange.\"** Aohane receives grudging respect—they clearly have culture, philosophy, beautiful arts. But the Pavonines don't fit the Five Natures, their magic is different, and their isolationism prevents real understanding.\n\n**\"Their display-culture is vanity.\"** Zhiran's emphasis on restraint makes kagami look like peacock posturing. They miss that for Pavonines, display is authenticity—hiding one's gifts is the shameful act.\n\n**\"They trade with us because they need us.\"** Zhiran assumes Aohane's limited trade indicates dependence. In truth, Aohane is entirely self-sufficient; trade is a strategic choice, not necessity.",
