      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Others Believe About Zhiran**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Others Believe About Zhiran**\n\n**\"They absorbed the beastfolk's magic.\"** Göran and Drakhar both believe Zhiran stole magical knowledge from integrated beastfolk, using civilized comforts to drain authentic power. There's a grain of truth—knowledge did flow through integration—but the framing ignores that integration was often genuinely chosen.\n\n**\"The river-folk are mongrels.\"** Both barbarian peoples view species-mixing with contempt. They assume integration weakens both species, producing confused half-beings without the strengths of either. The actual mixed-species households of Zhiran would confound them.\n\n**\"Their emperor is a puppet of Satyr mages.\"** Goryun and the barbarian peoples often assume the Yueming dynasty is secretly controlled by its magical advisors. The reality is more banal: the court is controlled by whoever can navigate its Byzantine politics, and magical power is one factor among many.",
