    {
      "id": "b64ff879-06ff-455d-b974-01d43d970cd9",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Göran Believes About Others**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Göran Believes About Others**\n\n**\"Settled peoples have lost their SOULs.\"** Göran spirituality holds that khuur—the eternal wind, the running spirit—requires movement. People who settle are spiritually dead, their SOULs stagnating instead of running free. They genuinely pity the river-folk.\n\n**\"Drakhar Felines are honorless ambushers.\"** The ancient enmity between Lupine and Feline extends to the barbarian peoples. Göran warriors consider Feline tactics—ambush, withdrawal, individual glory-seeking—to be cowardly. A proper enemy fights in the open, pack against pack.\n\n**\"Integrated Lupines are traitors.\"** Lupines who have joined Zhiran, taken up farming or trade, are considered spiritually dead—and worse, they chose it. They abandoned the khuur. The Lupines of Beifang know that returning to the steppe would mean death.",
