    {
      "id": "4266a3fc-6418-461b-bed2-b40c8f0bfe20",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Others Believe About Göran**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Others Believe About Göran**\n\n**\"They have no culture, only violence.\"** Zhiran, Goryun, and the Tieravel peoples all underestimate Göran society. The intricate clan relationships, the oral traditions, the spiritual practices around the eternal wind—none of this registers. They see only the raids.\n\n**\"A unified horde would be unstoppable.\"** Everyone fears Göran unification. The great khans of the past nearly broke Zhiran. But outsiders overestimate both the likelihood and the durability of unification. The same pack dynamics that allow rapid consolidation also lead to rapid fracture when the khan dies.\n\n**\"They eat their dead.\"** A persistent myth in multiple cultures. Göran burial practices involve exposure to wind and sky, which outsiders have garbled into cannibalism.",
