    {
      "id": "237ebcd8-1a56-4da9-9d9f-be08183873b3",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Drakhar Believes About Others**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Drakhar Believes About Others**\n\n**\"Flatlanders cannot understand lungta.\"** Drakhar Felines view anyone from lower elevations as spiritually impoverished—unable to understand the vertical axis that connects earth to height to ancestors. This includes integrated Felines in Zhiran, who have \"abandoned their lungta.\"\n\n**\"Göran Lupines are honorless pack-thinkers.\"** The Feline contempt for Lupine tactics mirrors the reverse. Felines value individual glory, the dramatic raid, the personal kill. Lupine coordination seems like surrendering individual identity.\n\n**\"The river-folk's walls prove their weakness.\"** Drakhar interprets Zhiran's fortifications as evidence they cannot fight in the open. The practical effectiveness of those walls against Feline raids is grudgingly acknowledged; the reason for them is not.",
