      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Others Believe About Drakhar**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Others Believe About Drakhar**\n\n**\"They worship the mineral.\"** Outsiders often assume lungta-worship is simple resource-veneration, missing that the mineral represents an entire cosmological framework about ancestors, heights, and spiritual connection.\n\n**\"Pride politics prevent any real threat.\"** Zhiran's strategic assumption is that Feline individualism prevents large-scale coordination. This is usually true—but it underestimates how quickly prides can unite when given sufficient cause, such as a Zhiran invasion.\n\n**\"Their mobility gear could be copied.\"** Zhiran engineers have tried for centuries. The gear responds to Feline SOUL-signatures; outsiders who use it tend to die. This isn't just skill—it's spiritual compatibility that cannot be replicated.",
