      "name": "**What Goryun Believes About Others**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Goryun Believes About Others**\n\n**\"Zhiran needs us more than we need them.\"** Goryun's defensive confidence sometimes tips into overestimation. Their mountain passes are strong, but they are not invulnerable. The Zhiran court's occasional noises about \"bringing Goryun into the fold\" are dismissed too easily.\n\n**\"Our Compact proves species cooperation is possible.\"** Goryun holds up its three-species partnership as evidence that integration can work without Zhiran's hierarchies. They underestimate how much their success depends on specific historical circumstances—and how much their small beastfolk minorities actually shape policy.",
