      "id": "45ddf66e-c9b4-4ac4-850a-d39cdc3be2b6",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Others Believe About Goryun**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Others Believe About Goryun**\n\n**\"They are Zhiran's rebellious children.\"** Zhiran views Goryun as a province that never quite accepted its place. The idea that Goryun represents an alternative model—not rebellion but genuine independence—is uncomfortable to acknowledge.\n\n**\"Their humans are dangerous precedent.\"** Zhiran's human population is carefully integrated into the Five Natures framework. Goryun's human-majority population, governing successfully, suggests humans might not need beastfolk oversight. This is spoken about carefully, if at all.",
