      "name": "**What Aohane Believes About Others**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Aohane Believes About Others**\n\n**\"Mammals hide themselves out of spiritual weakness.\"** The Pavonine emphasis on kagami—true display, authentic radiance—makes mammalian cultures seem cowardly. Zhiran's restraint, Goryun's discipline, even Göran's pack-identity—all look like failure to shine.\n\n**\"No one has anything we need.\"** Aohane's self-sufficiency breeds a certain arrogance. Their trade is strategic positioning, not necessity. They sometimes underestimate how much their beautiful goods have made them dependent on continued peaceful relations.\n\n**\"We are fundamentally different.\"** The Pavonines know they are the only avian beastfolk. This uniqueness has bred isolation—the assumption that no one can understand them, so why try to explain?",
