    {
      "id": "a94e8851-8006-4bf7-9f32-837cc2ade964",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Thalassic Humans Believe About Themselves**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Thalassic Humans Believe About Themselves**\n\n**\"We built civilization from nothing.\"** The founding myths of every Flame-city involve desperate refugees creating something new. The reality—that they stand on Imperial colonial foundations, using land taken from beastfolk—has been conveniently forgotten.\n\n**\"The Flames prove our right to exist.\"** The Civic Flame is both weapon and theology. Thalassic humans genuinely believe their SOUL-pooling represents a unique spiritual achievement that justifies their presence. They do not consider that the beastfolk might view this \"achievement\" as an abomination.\n\n**\"We have been here a thousand years.\"** True, but the beastfolk were here for ten thousand before that. The human sense of ancient settlement is shallow by Tieravel standards.",
