    {
      "id": "8d93a3d2-3e1f-4f5c-8b51-496dc0de03df",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Thalassic Humans Believe About Beastfolk**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Thalassic Humans Believe About Beastfolk**\n\n**\"They would exterminate us if they could.\"** Many Thalassic humans believe the Beasttide represented beastfolk nature—that given the chance, the \"beast-men\" would finish the job. This ignores that the Beasttide *stopped*. The beastfolk chose to leave the coastal humans alive. The reasons are debated, but the restraint was real.\n\n**\"They cannot build cities.\"** Thalassic humans who have never visited New Gloria or Noctria assume beastfolk live in primitive conditions. The reality—that the beastfolk heartland has cities rivaling anything on the coast—would be shocking.\n\n**\"Their magic is instinct, not learning.\"** The sophisticated traditions of Hintida's High Magi, the specialized Dream-Walkers of Ceunant, the complex geomantic practices throughout the Brythonic sphere—none of this penetrates Thalassic stereotypes. Beastfolk magic is assumed to be savage and uncontrolled.\n\n**\"The Saltraeth are simply pirates.\"** The Sea-Clans are reduced to their raiding, ignoring their complex society, their spiritual relationship with the sea, and their role in liberating Tieravel during the Beasttide.",
