    {
      "id": "b930518e-f58e-41ef-a28d-9515d0b128fd",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Brythonic Beastfolk Believe About Humans**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Brythonic Beastfolk Believe About Humans**\n\n**\"They are all colonizers.\"** Tieravel beastfolk do not distinguish between Imperial conquerors and the Thalassic descendants who have lived on the coast for a millennium. Humans are humans. The gwraidd is elsewhere. They do not belong.\n\n**\"The Flames are perversions.\"** Orthodox beastfolk theology holds that SOUL-pooling is unnatural, a desperate human adaptation that corrupts the Primordial's purpose. The idea that humans might have created something genuinely new is uncomfortable.\n\n**\"They would conquer us again if they could.\"** The trauma of Imperial occupation echoes through beastfolk culture. Many assume human restraint is simply inability, not choice—that the Flames are rebuilt and waiting for their chance. The defensive mindset prevents genuine negotiation.\n\n**\"Human civilization is stolen from us.\"** Some beastfolk believe every human achievement is derivative—built on knowledge taken from beastfolk during the occupation. There is a grain of truth (the Empire did absorb beastfolk learning), but the claim often extends to things humans developed independently.",
