    {
      "id": "f453ef54-af5f-4dcf-9f26-9c8acee74e48",
      "storyId": "55fed642-2517-4046-865d-17e3ade46d48",
      "name": "**What Both Spheres Get Wrong About the Marchlands**",
      "type": "concept",
      "description": "**What Both Spheres Get Wrong About the Marchlands**\n\n**\"It's contested because no one wants it.\"** Both humans and beastfolk sometimes assume the Marchlands are wasteland, strategically unimportant. In fact, the region contains valuable resources, strategic passes, and populations who have built their own cultures from the wreckage.\n\n**\"Marchlanders have no loyalty.\"** Both sides accuse Marchland communities of mercenary flexibility—trading information, switching sides, playing both powers. From the Marchland perspective, this is survival. Loyalty to distant capitals that have never protected you is a luxury.\n\n**\"The border is stable.\"** It isn't. The line shifts constantly through small raids, land grabs, and demographic pressure. What looks like stalemate from the great capitals is actually constant low-level conflict for those who live there.",
